Description: @DEFAULTS_Description

Name: Pirate Monarch's Treasure Throne
Description: This golden throne might offend the minimalist crowd. But who cares what they think? You're rich!

Name: Pirate Monarch's Chandelier
Description: This solid gold octopus lamp was commissioned in loving memory of all the crewmates who met their end in battle against a much, much larger octopus.

Name: Pirate Monarch's Wall Sconce
Description: It's traditional for a pirate interior decorator, on her deathbed, to donate her skull toward the creation of a gilded six-skull lamp like this one. They are said to bring tremendous good luck.

Name: Pirate Monarch's Inverted Wall Sconce
Description: This inverted lighting fixture has the opposite meaning from the original. It's sometimes sent to enemy pirates as threats; actually hanging one up is a show of bravery and defiance.

Name: Pirate Monarch's Beloved Birdbath
Description: This pampered, jewel-toned waterfowl was a gift from a South Asian prince. Housed in an open birdbath, he's not caged in; he just knows this is the best seat in the house.

Name: Pirate Monarch's Gilded Cannon
Description: Some might take this richly-ornamented cannon as a mere objet d'art. They will be very surprised the first time they try to board your house.

Name: Pirate Monarch's Treasure Map
Description: A richly-detailed, full-color treasure map. So detailed in fact, you might actually find riches where the X marks the spot. The hunt is on!

Name: Pirate Monarch's Octopus Vase
Description: This porcelain and gold vase is a treasure worthy of any museum. But the real treasure is what you've buried at the bottom.

Name: "Ocean's Daughter" Painting
Description: A painting of a mermaid, in an elaborate gilded frame. It feels as though the painter was yearning for a long-lost love.

Name: Pirate Monarch's Hoard
Description: Not your full hoard, of course. The table would collapse under the weight of that much treasure.

Name: Pirate Monarch's Steering Wheel
Description: Grab hold. Close your eyes. Recapture the feeling of sailing, free as the ocean breeze.

Name: Pirate Monarch's Golden Plaque
Description: A lifetime achievement award from the International Brotherhood of Pirates. The award from the Sisterhood of Pirates is even more impressive.

Name: Haunted Candelabra
Description: From ghastly, grim and graves unhallow, light a candle rendered from a dead man’s tallow.

Name: Scapegrace Jack’s Lascivious Lantern
Description: Sextons and gravediggers say the old lech could wink in such a manner as to set a cadaver to shivers and blushing.

Name: Scapegrace Jack’s Happy Lantern
Description: The miscreant ne’er-do-well was happily damned and damnably happy. You’d smile too if you fooled the Devil himself!

Name: Scapegrace Jack’s Frightful Lantern
Description: Welcome in neither Heaven nor Hell, for Scapegrace Jack fills gourds with ghost-fire to light his way through the spaces between.

Name: Scapegrace Jack’s Fatuous Lantern
Description: Oh, that scallywag rascal, that tatterdemalion, that mischief-making scapegrace! Oh how a perverse thought or plotted prank would screw up his face into a ghoulish smirk.

Name: Bubbling Cauldron
Description: Adder’s fork and blind-worm’s sting, lizard’s leg and owlet’s wing. For a charm of powerful trouble, like a hell-broth boil and bubble.

Name: The Conjuring Crystal
Description: Through the glimmer and glamor of the crystal ball, a spectre giggles, “Pins and needles, needles and pins — the happy skull is the skull who grins!”

Name: Vermiculated Curtains
Description: Worm-eaten fabric of burial shrouds ward against all manner of ghosts. Or does it invites them in? Fie! Tis hard to recall the finer points of spirit lore.

Name: Enchanted Broom
Description: No good witch is caught, dead or not, without a trusty broom. Enchant it you must, to battle the dust, that gathers in your room.

Name: Potion-Maker’s Kit
Description: Any conjurer, wise man, or cunning woman will tell you — a smile and a nefariously brewed potion will get you much further than just a smile.

Name: Stolen Gravestone
Description: Loamy soil comforts the wicked. A plundered tombstone makes homey decor for the perverse.

Name: Puppergeist
Description: A canine so faithful they don't require a physical form to be there for you. Plus, no allergies or shedding!

Name: Sungleam Throne
Description: Do remember to wipe the undead filth off your boots before placing feet on the silken pillow.

Name: The Baron's Chandelier
Description: An essential chandelier for the up-and-coming noble, dripping with crystals and a sense of importance.

Name: Resplendency
Description: Elegance defined in candelabra form. Place it on a table or pedestal, it will shine brightly in either case.

Name: The Baroness's Light
Description: Adorned with all her favorite jewels, the fixture illuminates the walls of the halls of many a Barony.

Name: Sunset Baldachin
Description: A canopy of crimson and gold used to frame what is most precious to the homeowner.

Name: Sunrise Curtains
Description: Emblazoned with a triumphant sun rising, this curtain set lets in just enough light to illuminate the woven golden threads.

Name: Aureate Plinth
Description: This dais is strong enough to hold any petitioner to the throne, no matter how they tremble in its presence.

Name: Goldenlight Pedestal
Description: A pedestal of immense value, perhaps even more tasteful than what is placed atop it.

Name: Convergence Chandelier
Description: The glitter of the Gleamite crystals fills the whole house with warmth and joviality, just like the Winter Wanderer would want.

Name: Convergence Garland
Description: A beautiful creation of purple cloth, poinsettias, and Gleamite crystals to signal the shift in season.

Name: Convergence Gingerbread Cottage
Description: A delightfully-decorated and edible home made of cookies and candy. Just make sure it doesn't go stale.

Name: Tree of Light
Description: A tree shining with Gleamite crystals and surrounded by presents from loved ones. The lights and gifts represents the spirit of the holiday.

Name: Convergence Mistletoe
Description: Known for blooming flowers even during the harshest winters, hanging a bundle above your doorway is said to foster peace and love to those who walk beneath it.

Name: Convergence Presents
Description: What could possibly be wrapped inside? Did the Winter Wanderer leave these? Which ones are for me?

Name: Convergence Poinsettia
Description: A collection of purple flowers that blooms only in winter, signaling the time of Convergence upon Aeternum.

Name: Convergence Snowman
Description: A snowy friend for the wintertide, adorned with Gleamite to shine brightly in the dark and cold. Just don't let him stand in direct sunlight.

Name: Convergence Wreath
Description: A wreath that welcomes all to the holiday of Winter Convergence, a time of cheer and fear in Aeternum.

Name: Festive Deer
Description: Complete with his own purple scarf to keep warm to threat of Forever Winter. He loves to be pet on his warm, red nose.

Name: Lunar Hanging Lantern
Description: This isn't simply a single lantern. It is singularly the most perfect lantern to perfect your new year.

Name: Lunar Wall Lanterns
Description: A string of multiple red and gold paper lanterns to light your home and your path to success.

Name: Lunar Firecrackers
Description: Once lit, these put on quite the spectacle. Best to cover your ears, as the crackling can be deafening.

Name: Golden Foo Dog
Description: A stalwart guardian of houses far and wide. Yours is extra special because it is now protecting you.

Name: Sunrise Parade Lion Head
Description: One mask to signify the beginning of a new year. Look deep into its eyes and see the pride of the lion.

Name: Sunset Parade Lion Head
Description: One mask to signify the end of a year - and see that it was lived well.

Name: Warm Red Paper Fans
Description: Finely crafted paper fans of red and gold. For a splash of color on your wall and of good luck for the year to come.

Name: Welcoming Red Paper Fans
Description: An arrangement of beautiful fans made of delicate paper and gold. Hang them on your wall to welcome the new year in style.

Name: Lunar Tiger Shadowbox
Description: The carving of a majestic tiger, projected out with a candle's flame.

Name: Lunar New Year Tiger
Description: A mystical being that has gifted you with its presence and its protection - and doesn't mind a scratch behind the ears now and again.

Name: Romantic Swooning Couch
Description: A curved and elegant love-seat, for all your swooning needs.

Name: Romantic Heart Chair
Description: An arched, plush chair for sitting and fantasizing about the finer aspects of romance.

Name: Romantic Candelabra
Description: A lovely light, brimming with roses, to set the mood for any kind of date on Aeternum.

Name: Romantic Sconce
Description: Silver and lavender crafted tenderly, and shines as warm as the light in your heart.

Name: Love Letter Desk
Description: The perfect place to pen your feelings and desires for your sweetheart.

Name: Tray of Love Potions
Description: A wide array of bubbly brews to bring out the love in you.

Name: Exotic Bubble Bath
Description: A florid clawfoot tub filled with lavish bubbles. A delightful way to prepare before a tryst.

Name: Romantic Bouquet
Description: A beautiful arrangement of deep-red roses, blossoming as strongly as your love.

Name: Black Bear Pelt Rug
Description: A bear skin rug so dark it almost looks purple. Perfect for lounging seductively on in your own bare skin.

Name: Romantic Dinner Table
Description: The perfect place where two lovers can gaze longingly at each other by charming candlelight.

Name: Springtime Rattan Chair
Description: The pillows were hand-embroidered by some of the finest furnishers in Windsward.

Name: Springtime Ceiling Lantern
Description: The paper of this lantern resembles flower petals. The glow it emits is cool and light.

Name: Springtime Wall Lantern
Description: The pastel hues of the paper makes a room look like it is blushing.

Name: Springtime Rug
Description: A pop of color for even the most dour of Brightwood homes.

Name: Springtime Ceiling Flowers
Description: Two baskets filled to the brim with fragrant flowers for sweetening the air of any home, even in Reekwater.

Name: Spring Floral Blower
Description: A gentle device that sends colorful flower petals up into the air. Just start the propellers and watch it go!

Name: Springtime Curtains
Description: Crocheted silks and fresh flowers, this drapery makes for the perfect backdrop to an Aeternum wedding.

Name: Springtime Tub O' Flowers
Description: Bunches of brilliant, blooming buds in a basket. Both bountiful and beautiful.

Name: Springtime Rattan Table
Description: It doesn't support much, but it sure does look nice, doesn't it?

Name: Springtime Wreath
Description: A collection of colorful flowers that can be found across Aeternum, picked and arranged just for you.

Name: Springtime Bunny
Description: This hare loves to wear his springtime attire.

Name: Cosmic Armillary Dial
Description: Concentric circles form a spinning, rotating model of the cosmos to view and admire.

Name: Astronomical Astrolabe
Description: A model of the known universe. You can use it to measure the distance of the sun and stars above, but can it help unravel the mysteries of Aeternum.

Name: Tarot Game Table
Description: A popular game on Aeternum involving the four suits of tarot cards. It both cures boredom and predicts your future.

Name: Fateful Hourglass
Description: The sands of mortality may be paused on Aeternum, but these sands do anything but stand still.

Name: Palmistry Statue
Description: For when you need an extra hand when performing palm readings.

Name: Fortune Scrying Table
Description: Gaze into and ponder the orb and you may yet see the future.

Name: Zodiac Tapestry
Description: A well-used tapestry depicting the cycle of the western Zodiac. While lovely, it makes you feel like you are being watched.

Name: Astral Chandelier
Description: An elaborate mobile with various planets and stars, engraved with Zodiac symbols.

Name: Pig of Mystery
Description: Who is that mysterious swine, and why does it look so dapper? Is it filthy rich?

Name: Tempting Treasure
Description: Do. Not. Touch.

Name: Storyteller's Chair
Description: This imposing chair strikes fear in even the stoutest hearts. The smoke really sells it, even if it makes your eyes water a bit.

Name: Fantastical Seat
Description: Comfortable enough to sit for hours at a time. It may be a trick of the light, but did those clawed feet just move?

Name: Everflame Chandelier
Description: A golden phoenix posed in glory. Even if extinguished, the brilliant flame rekindles itself mere moments later.

Name: Wyrmbreath Sconce
Description: A stone sconce carved with integrate details of a scaled beast. The intense heat and light belie its small size.

Name: Storyteller's Game
Description: Everything you need for an evening of thrilling adventure! Just add friends, a bit of imagination, and ale. Lots of ale.

Name: Tapestry of the 'Perfect Balance'
Description: With all roles working in harmony, any foe can be defeated. That is, if everyone can pay attention long enough.

Name: Fantastical Table
Description: Gather your party 'round this handsome table, to share a meal, or venture forth on an epic quest of your imagination.

Name: Iron-Song Music Box
Description: A new twist on what a music box can do, with just a flip of the lid you can hear some heavy music. Ignore the sparks. That's normal.

Name: Iron-Song Spiked Chair
Description: A supremely stabby and skeletal steel seat. Superb for sitting stoically.

Name: Iron-Song Drum Chandelier
Description: An elk-skin drum lit by flickering candles. Even just looking at it makes you feel the beat.

Name: Iron-Song Drum Side Table
Description: You can bang out a heavy beat one minute, then display something awesome the next.

Name: Iron-Song Hand Sculpture
Description: A decorative piece to show how hardcore you really are. So hardcore, that hand might not be a sculpture after all.

Name: Iron-Song Axe Lute
Description: A stringed instrument in the shape of a double axe. You can defeat your enemies, then immediately play a song about it.

Name: Iron-Song Spiked Guitar
Description: A dangerous musical device with red runes etched upon it. Try not to get stabbed by the spikes when you play it.

Name: Iron-Song Lyre Shelf
Description: Great for displaying things, just watch out for the sharp metal prongs.

Name: Iron-Song Painting
Description: Immortalized in oils rides a skeletal knight upon a mighty steed. Axe in hand and ready for battle. All he's missing is the war music.

Name: Iron-Song Tour Tapestry
Description: An embroidered cloth, forever encapsulating the memories of your favorite Aeternum music tour.

Name: Rising-Fire Throne
Description: A regal seat with golden plumes and plush cushioning. Sitting upon this throne lets everyone know who rules the roost in your home.

Name: Rising-Fire Feathered Chandelier
Description: An ornate ceiling light made of blazing phoenix feathers that make for a never-ending light source.

Name: Rising-Fire Brazier
Description: A golden fire pit in the shape of a phoenix rising in glory. Perfect to gather round with friends for both light and warmth.

Name: Rising-Fire Winged Lantern
Description: Glowing bright, this lantern depicts a phoenix holding a pure white sphere, signifying the purity of its spirit.

Name: Rising-Fire Bouquet
Description: A lovely and very hot arrangement of phoenix feathers aflame in a stylish vase. Careful not to place it near anything flammable.

Name: Rising-Fire Pedestal
Description: A grand golden display pillar that you can place almost anything upon. Just be sure whatever it may be is also just as flashy.

Name: Rising-Fire Room Divider
Description: A creation of stained-glass that shows a phoenix wreathed in flames. Beautiful for decorating your home. Terrible for privacy while changing.

Name: Rising-Fire Glass Art
Description: A glass art piece depicting a rising phoenix in warm hues. Hang it on your wall or over your windows and make all your neighbors envious.

Name: Rising-Fire Rug
Description: Soft on bare feet and pleasing to the eye, this rug portrays a burning sun.

Name: Glorious Phoenix
Description: A mythical bird of death and rebirth. Its glorious plumage emits heat and fire, but it will not burn the ones it trusts if they were to pet it.

Name: Aegyptus Sarcophagus
Description: A functional piece of art that may or may not still be full of its haunted contents, treasure, or both.

Name: Aegyptus Carved Bench
Description: Finery is a must-have for any desert ruler, and this bench inlaid with gold and gemstones fits the bill.

Name: Aegyptus Uraeus Canopic Jar
Description: The symbol of an upright cobra is iconic for royalty and the divine. So there are very likely some pharaoh guts within. Best not to open it.

Name: Aegyptus Horus Canopic Jar
Description: A regal hawk stands ready to guard whatever you may wish to store in here. Typically, it's organs.

Name: Aegyptus Anubis Canopic Jar
Description: The face of the jackal was the face of the god of death. So that gives you a pretty good idea of what might be inside this jar.

Name: Aegyptus Ancients Canopic Jar
Description: Some people tend to mix up the Ancients and the Egyptians. And while they have some similarities, they were very different in a multitude of ways.

Name: Aegyptus Bastet Pedestal
Description: A feline friend for your home that requires no looking after besides the occasional polish.

Name: Aegyptus Horus Scrolls
Description: What could they possibly say? And what could they have to do with the Ancients of Aeternum?

Name: Aegyptus Scarab Table Lamp
Description: This scarab holds aloft a glimmering light source for all to see and admire.

Name: Aegyptus Cobra Wall Lantern
Description: A brazier of fire atop a golden cobra of the desert. The fire doesn't help with the heat, but is excellent with lighting a room.

Name: Aegyptus Sculptural Table
Description: Allows for the display of honored treasures picked up in your adventures across Aeternum, or partaking of a fine meal with friends.

Name: Nightmare Horned Chandelier
Description: Lashed and bound, these horns and skulls carry candles to bring light to a dark home.

Name: Nightmare Web-Framed Insects
Description: A small collection of the creepy crawlies of Aeternum. Framed in bones and webs, any spider would be proud to show these off.

Name: Nightmare Formaldehyde Jars
Description: While the chemicals are extremely toxic to the living, they are capable of preserving the dead for centuries. Priceless for science, research, and giving your home that extra creepy feel.

Name: Nightmare Grimoire Lectern
Description: Dare you approach and open the book? Be prepared for the horrors you might unleash.

Name: Nightmare Loxodonta Skull Display
Description: A skull with large, low tusks, and humongous sinus openings set very high. If you didn't already know it was the skull of an elephant, you never would never guess.

Name: Nightmare Alligatoridae Skull Display
Description: Alligators have rounded snouts, while crocodiles have more pointed ones. So knowing that, it is pretty easy to tell which one this is.

Name: Nightmare Wall Masks
Description: Sharp teeth and glaring eyes make for the perfect intimidating home decor. If you stare at them too long, you might notice them staring right back.

Name: Nightmare Spider Wreath
Description: A wreath made of dried autumnal vegetation, and spiderwebs. While the wood that makes the wreath is dead, you cannot say the same for the spider.

Name: Performing Spiderling
Description: A very friendly and well-trained spider companion. It knows many tricks and is happy to perform them, as long as it remains well fed.

Name: Dusk Sylph Bed
Description: Lavend'r bedding both soft and gleaming, maketh the canvas in which thee may craft dreaming.

Name: Dusk Sylph Sofa
Description: Soft and plush and beckoning thee to rest.  P'rfect f'r hosting any fine spirit'd guest.

Name: Dusk Sylph Glass Bookcase
Description: Opulent glass hides precious trinkets so rare.  Craft'd of dusk spirit wood of the finest and fair.

Name: Dusk Sylph Glass Chandelier
Description: Soft blue hues lighteth thy way home.  Gentle butt'rflies ensure thou art not alone.

Name: Convergence Boots and Slippers
Description: Not one, not two, but three pairs of warm and comfy footwear to keep your toes warm this winter holiday.

Name: Convergence Coat Rack
Description: Coats are a must in the freezing winter season, and so is a coat rack to hang them up and dry off for the next snowy excursion.

Name: Convergence Cocoa Platter
Description: Hot drinks are a must when the weather gets cold, and decadent chocolate and cream, cinnamon and spices, makes them even better.

Name: Convergence Rocking Horse
Description: A classic children's toy, adorned with bells that jingle so sweetly when you give this horse a gentle push.

Name: Festive Winter Kitty
Description: This snowy furred feline is purrfectly happy loafing by the fire, or chilling in the snow. In either case, they adore pets from you.

Name: Open Rickety Bookcase
Description: Lots of space to place all kinds of things, it doesn’t always have to be books.

Name: Low Apothecary Cabinet
Description: A low-slung cabinet of drawers, for keeping your heaviest treasures.

Name: Oak Wine Cask
Description: The flavor profile of wine aged in Aeternian oak barrels has been described by connoisseurs as "demented".

Name: Wicker Basket
Description: Ideal for holding fruit, laundry, or decorative wooden orbs.

Name: Old Wooden Bunk Bed
Description: What is better than one bed? Two beds. One on top of the other!

Name: Old Straw Cot
Description: A simple cot made of straw and skins. Perfectly comfortable, if you don't mind the occasional stab from a prickly piece of grass.

Name: Old Wooden Full Bed
Description: Classic. Wooden. Only semi-comfortable. But it will do for a quick nap.

Name: Stone Cairn
Description: Several dark stones stacked to make an artful tower. Looking at it makes you feel like you accomplished something.

Name: Rickety Wooden Chair
Description: This chair looks like it might be on its last leg. And you might be too if you hazard to sit in it.

Name: Rickety Wooden Stool
Description: Perfect for stepping on to reach high places, then falling off and breaking your neck.

Name: Old Desk Chair
Description: A simple wooden chair you used to see in schools or libraries. Is it comfortable? No idea.

Name: Old Log Stool
Description: Just a simple log. Literally the least amount of work put into crafting a stool in the history of wood.

Name: Grey Streamer Curtains
Description: Cleverly repurposed from the debris of one of Aeternum's many, many shipwrecks.

Name: Bedsheet Curtains
Description: Simple lengths you can string up on your wall or window. Your neighbors will never know that these used to be your bedsheets.

Name: Tied-Back Curtain
Description: A simple curtain tied back with a length of rope. The effect is surprisingly charming.

Name: Iron Cup
Description: Completely safe to drink from. I swear!

Name: Iron Pan
Description: A cast iron pan. Grandmas everywhere love them. They don't make 'em like they used to.

Name: Unsettling Branch Wreath
Description: Look at the pattern. Now look away. Now look back - have the twigs shifted position?

Name: Protective Straw Wreath
Description: This little guy will guard your door. Any would-be burglar will run for their lives upon seeing it.

Name: Squared Circle Twig Wreath
Description: The geometry of this twig wreath is pleasing to the eye.

Name: Wall Woven Wicker Wreath
Description: Aeternians have been weaving these traditional winter decorations for as long as anyone can remember.

Name: Garlic Bulb Wreath
Description: Vampire proof. And strangely, also keeps your friends from visiting. Is it because of the stench, or are they vampires?

Name: Glass Demijohn Jug
Description: Just the thing you needed for your pennies. Before long, it is going to be impossible to lift.

Name: Decorative Glass Bottle
Description: This bottle will go perfectly with the shiplap you just installed.

Name: Dark Wicker-Wrapped Jug
Description: Aeternum has adopted the European tradition of wrapping glass bottles in wicker to prevent breakage and spoilage.

Name: Light Wicker-Wrapped Jug
Description: The contents of this basket-wrapped jug are a complete mystery.

Name: Square Earthenware Jar
Description: This jar isn't much to look at, but it gets the jar job done.

Name: Round Earthenware Jar
Description: This humble clay jar is elevated by a decorative dribble of shiny glaze.

Name: Firewood Pile
Description: The wood is cured to perfection for a clean, long-lasting burn.

Name: Hanging Sack
Description: Whatever is in this sack, it would be disastrous if it touched the ground.

Name: Burlap Sack
Description: What's in this sack? Potatoes? Beans? Diamonds?... Might be diamonds.

Name: Cluttered Dishes
Description: They might be messy, but at least they're clean.

Name: Old Placesetting
Description: A well-worn place setting that has held years of delicious meals.

Name: Candle Cluster
Description: These candles were just friends, at first, but they got too close. Now they are fused together into a super candle.

Name: Rusty Iron Candelabra
Description: Three tall candles, burning bright, keeping back the endless night.

Name: Rusty Iron Lantern
Description: This lantern glows with love. But don't touch it. Its love could burn.

Name: Rusty Hanging Lantern
Description: A simple lantern hanging from above, shining light into the highest nooks and crannies.

Name: Wooden Wall Torch
Description: This wooden torch is blazing with glorious fire. Let's hope your house doesn't want to feel the same way.

Name: Iron Jug
Description: An old iron jug, usually used for milk. But if you wanted to, you could put all sorts of things in this.

Name: Old Books Row Short
Description: These books are your all-time favorites, and deserve a place of special honor.

Name: Old Books Stack
Description: You haven't had time to put these books back on the shelf. Perhaps you're too busy reading.

Name: Old Books Row Long
Description: These books are in remarkably good condition, considering the sorry state of the ship they came from.

Name: Unsettling Note
Description: You don't remember writing this, but it's your handwriting. And it contains all your deepest fears and darkest secrets.

Name: Sentimental Note
Description: Waterstained and nearby illegible. That's all right; you committed the words to heart long ago.

Name: To-Do List
Description: You can already cross off the first entry: "Make a to-do list". You're so productive!

Name: Impossible Geometry Notes
Description: Looks like some notes about geometry… But not any kind of geometry you've ever seen.

Name: Passive-aggressive Wall Note
Description: A note left from your roommate telling you to put your clothes away. Wait, don't you live alone?

Name: Unpaid Parking Tickets
Description: Look at all these tickets! You need to remember to move your cart on street sweeper day.

Name: Paper-wrapped Parcel
Description: What could be inside? Some ancient instinct is warning you not to open it.

Name: Very Important Papers
Description: A stack of very important papers, for the attention of a very important person - you.

Name: Powder Horn
Description: Contains black gunpowder. Keep the lid on, and don't bring it into the kitchen.

Name: Small Drum
Description: The ancient remains of drums like this one have been unearthed all over Aeternum.

Name: Hanging Pottery
Description: Best to keep the inside of that pot up and out of sight. You don't wanna know what's in it…

Name: Round Birdcage
Description: A cute wicker birdcage. Unfortunately, the bird seems to have flown away.

Name: Brown Bear Pelt Rug
Description: A soft and fuzzy bear rug to warm your bare feet, or to lounge upon seductively. Or both.

Name: Fraying Cloth Rug
Description: Technically meets the bare minimum requirements of a rug.

Name: Fishnet Rug
Description: What a creative use for a fishing net. Sweeping dirt under it is pointless, though.

Name: Rustic Wooden Scrollcase
Description: Full of cubbies for all your paper, vellum, and papyrus. Clay tablets, too, if you're into the classics.

Name: Assorted Bottles
Description: Colorful bottles for any occasion and for any substance, from spices to poison. Just don't get them mixed up.

Name: Rickety Wooden Wall Shelf
Description: The beauty is not in the shelf itself, but in the possibilities it contains.

Name: Small Rustic Cabinet
Description: Perfect for a very organized person. A place for everything, and everything in its place.

Name: Rustic Stone Stove
Description: Keep that fire in its place, which is inside this stove.

Name: Hewn Log Storage Chest
Description:
A chest that grants access to your storage, and increases your storage by {[HouseItems.House_HousingItem_Storage_T1_ChestOldLog.StorageBonus / 10]} weight when placed in your home. 
It won't keep out any thieves, though.

Name: Old Wood Storage Chest
Description:
A chest that grants access to your storage, and increases your storage by {[HouseItems.House_HousingItem_Storage_T1_ChestOldWood.StorageBonus / 10]} weight when placed in your home. 
Perfectly serviceable.

Name: Mossy Rock Storage Chest
Description:
A chest that grants access to your storage, and increases your storage by {[HouseItems.House_HousingItem_Storage_T1_ChestRock.StorageBonus / 10]} weight when placed in your home. 
Cleverly disguised as a humble rock.

Name: Iron Storage Chest
Description:
A chest that grants access to your storage, and increases your storage by {[HouseItems.House_HousingItem_Storage_T2_ChestIron.StorageBonus / 10]} weight when placed in your home. 
Built solid and sturdy.

Name: Hunter Storage Chest
Description:
A chest that grants access to your storage, and increases your storage by {[HouseItems.House_HousingItem_Storage_T2_ChestPrimal.StorageBonus / 10]} weight when placed in your home. 
Holds your things just fine, and doubles as a canoe if you are in a pinch.

Name: Stone Storage Chest
Description:
A chest that grants access to your storage, and increases your storage by {[HouseItems.House_HousingItem_Storage_T2_ChestStone.StorageBonus / 10]} weight when placed in your home. 
Just how old is this thing, exactly?

Name: Polished Marble Storage Chest
Description:
A chest that grants access to your storage, and increases your storage by {[HouseItems.House_HousingItem_Storage_T4_ChestAncient.StorageBonus / 10]} weight when placed in your home. 
Scholars have not yet translated these Ancient runes.

Name: Cursed Storage Chest
Description:
A chest that grants access to your storage, and increases your storage by {[HouseItems.House_HousingItem_Storage_T4_ChestMacab.StorageBonus / 10]} weight when placed in your home. 
Definitely cursed, 100%.

Name: Defiled Storage Chest of the Hare
Description:
A chest that grants access to your storage, and increases your storage by {[HouseItems.House_HousingItem_Storage_T4_ChestRabbit.StorageBonus / 10]} weight when placed in your home. 
How did a rabbit carry this?
Notes: Extremely rare drop from killing Corrupted Rabbits during event.

Description:
A chest that grants access to your storage, and increases your storage by {[HouseItems.House_HousingItem_Storage_T4_ChestSteel.StorageBonus / 10]} weight when placed in your home.

Name: Old Wood Dining Table
Description: A classic long dining table. So classic, in fact, that it might be the original from which all other dining tables evolved.

Name: Tree Stump Table
Description: A rustic table made from tree stumps. Perfect for planning adventures with your animal friends.

Name: Tree Stump Side Table
Description: A stump is a sort of proto-table already. You're just cutting out the middleman.

Name: Wooden Side Desk
Description: If you need some extra desk, well, here you go!

Name: Rickety Twig Table
Description: Who built this table? It isn't very well made. Is that even wood? Can it be trusted?

Name: Target Dummy
Description: This target dummy dreamed of becoming a scarecrow, but joined the army instead.

Name: Tarnished Silver Teacup
Description: Comes with a matching saucer. Sit in your favorite chair and savor the perfect cup of tea.

Name: Tall Green Ivy Trellis
Description: Look at these wonderful climbing vines. Something about them just makes you smile.

Name: Tall Pink Mandevilla Trellis
Description: Waxy blooms with a mild scent. People plant them more for the popping pink than anything else.

Name: Tall Red Cypress Trellis
Description: These vines grow really fast. So fast in fact, they might quickly outgrow their trellis. So trim the vines, but leave the flowers.

Name: Tall Orange Hibiscus Trellis
Description: The bright orange of these flowers reminds you of warm, sunny days. Even more so when they attract hummingbirds and butterflies.

Name: Tall White Moonflower Trellis
Description: The moonflower is prized for the bright white of its petals. But look; don't touch, or you might walk away with a rash.

Name: Tall Purple Wisteria Trellis
Description: Your home will not only look amazing with his trellis, but also smell amazingly sweet from the purple blooms.

Name: Short Green Ivy Trellis
Description: The glory days of this small vine are still ahead, but it might need a taller trellis to get there.

Name: Short Pink Mandevilla Trellis
Description: These blushing blooms don't really serve any purpose besides looking nice. And boy, do they ever!

Name: Short Red Cypress Trellis
Description: The scent of these flowers is very evocative of the forest. But the reds remind you instead of romance.

Name: Short Orange Hibiscus Trellis
Description: These flowers are often brewed to make an herbal tisane as a cure for what ails ya'.

Name: Short White Moonflower Trellis
Description: These flowers have hardly any scent. But that doesn't stop them from looking gorgeous.

Name: Short Purple Wisteria Trellis
Description: Some say you can make wine from these purple blooms. Others say they are toxic. Pick your poison, I guess.

Name: Broken Chime Post
Description: An old windchime holder with no windchimes. It looks like it is barely standing up.

Name: Lucky Wyrdwood
Description: One more potted plant couldn't hurt. Besides, how could you pass up a glowing one!

Name: Potted Wyrdwood
Description: House plants. For the home owner who wants kids but also wants to keep their gold.

Name: Song of the Wyrdwoods
Description: Give it water and sun. Plants are basically people with less complicated emotions.

Name: Open Book
Description: You're determined to finish this book before your friends spoil the ending.

Name: Sealed Scrolls
Description: You were warned not to open these sealed documents until you receive the signal.

Name: Scenic Painting of Lycopolis
Description: Built by the 19th Legion long ago, the now ruined aqueduct is teeming with wildlife, and treasure is rumored to be found amongst the treacherous rubble.

Name: Scenic Painting of the Deadwater Wastes
Description: Once a mighty Roman fortress and symbol of man's military power, the Acropolis now bends to nature; both natural and otherwise.

Name: Scenic Painting of the Frosted Floe
Description: The sound of water falling into Brightwood was great company.

Name: Scenic Painting of Gefyra Bridge
Description: It was so quiet on the cliffs nearby Rubble Shores.

Name: Scenic Painting of the Primal Lochan
Description: Ancient highways to rival that of Rome.

Name: Scenic Painting of Valle Tempus
Description: The bear's view of Everfall every morning.

Name: Scenic Painting of Shattered Mountain
Description: Painting is often a lonely activity, fitting for the Lonely Climb.

Name: Scenic Painting of the Bubbly Bay
Description: Sneaking past Eridanus wasn't easy, but the view was worth it.

Name: Scenic Painting of Brightwatch
Description: The snoring of bear cubs while you painted was comforting.

Name: Scenic Painting of Skysong Lagoon
Description: Not many places you can find yourself at peace in Ebonscale Reach.

Name: Scenic Painting of Old Northfork
Description: You can still smell Chef Giroux's cooking from far across Las Torres Bay.

Name: Scenic Painting of Antares
Description: Keeping a safe distance from the guardians was a good call.

Name: Scenic Painting of the Eternal Pool
Description: A rare view indeed, you should be proud of this masterpiece.

Name: Scenic Painting of Fay's Sorrow
Description: So that's what it feels like to be an acrobat.

Name: Scenic Painting of Soddenswale
Description: The gator did not appreciate you standing on his rock.

Name: Scenic Painting of Amrine Temple
Description: It was nice to see Barkimedes again.

Name: Scenic Painting of the Elin River
Description: Bison Island is always so peaceful this time of year.

Name: Scenic Painting of the Azoth Tree
Description: A true wonder of the natural world. Somebody should really make a list of those…

Name: Scenic Painting of the Imperial Palace
Description: It's a good thing the Imperial guards didn't stop you from getting this down on canvas.

Name: Scenic Painting of Old Elder's Bluff
Description: Remnants of a once great civilization. What caused their downfall?

Name: Scenic Painting of Deadman's Anchor
Description: The coast catches many ships, pieces of cliff jutting out like daggers ready to pierce the next hull.

Name: Scenic Painting of the Flooded Plains
Description: The rainwater from the north will continue the flood until the end of time.

Name: Scenic Painting of Lambent Muskeg
Description: The Siren calls to all in her domain.

Name: Scenic Painting of the Neptune's Fury
Description: The Storm's fury is unmatched, even by that of gods.

Name: Scenic Painting of Caminus
Description: The war effort never quiets in Caminus.

Name: Scenic Painting of Mangled Heights
Description: Even the Colossus cannot escape corruption.

Name: Scenic Painting of the Salty Marshes
Description: Even Snaggletooth knows better than to venture into the marsh.

Name: Scenic Painting from the Wyrdkissed Cliffs
Description: How can one ever do justice to the vibrant colors of Edengrove?

Name: Scenic Painting of Stonereach
Description: Many have started a new life through that arch.

Name: Scenic Painting of Mourning Bridge
Description: The canvas has water damage. Once it stops raining you should try again.

Name: Taxidermied Blue-blooded Barb
Description: This deepwater behemoth of Reekwater comes to the surface only once in its long lifetime.

Name: Taxidermied Varanus Mandje
Description: According to legend, this fish was once a prince, and could grant any wish in the world.

Name: Taxidermied Daemonaja
Description: Those eyes look almost human. Surely you're just imagining them following you around the room.

Name: Taxidermied Egede Serpe
Description: Catching this elusive creature is said to bring a year of good luck to the entire village.

Name: Dusty Armadillo
Description: A tamed armadillo from the harsh deserts of Brimstone. This big baby really loves belly scratches.

Name: Woodland Mastiff
Description: A faithful companion to lounge by the fire with you. Who doesn't love a dog in a hat! (Hint: Nobody!)

Name: Celestial Hare
Description: Brimming with awe, the vast expanse of the universe resides within the fur of this rabbit. And if you pet them, you might just feel it too.

Name: Ashen Tiger
Description: Neither light nor color can escape the deep darkness of its fur. But do you know what can? Love! And this big kitty needs lots of it.

Name: Silent Death Wolf
Description: An assassins' breed of wolf, cultivated for generations to silently keep pace with their owner, carrying spare weapons and poisons. The only downside is their breath is worse than their bite.

Name: Domiciliary Brown Bobcat
Description: Most bobcats would eat your face, but not this one. This one is spoiled and just wants to lounge and get neck scratches.

Name: Domiciliary Brown Elk Stag
Description: Stags tend to shed their antlers every year. Somehow, the next ones always grow bigger than the last.

Name: Domiciliary Brown Elk Doe
Description: A graceful doe with such a calming precedence. Seeing it curled up so sweetly makes you want to nap in the sunshine.

Name: Domiciliary Brown Mastiff
Description: A gentle giant of a dog that loves nothing more than to laze-about by the fire and get some good neck scratches.

Name: Domiciliary Pig Pink
Description: A pampered pig you can bring home to idle by your side and give some great belly rubs to.

Name: Domiciliary Brown Puma
Description: This puma is so calm and relaxed, it can be hard to remember that it could rip your throat out in a flash if it really wanted to.

Name: Domiciliary Brown Rabbit
Description: A sweet and gentle rabbit that just wants a little bit of love. Maybe a carrot or two.

Name: Domiciliary Brown Turkey
Description: This turkey is too sweet to cook for dinner. Dessert however…

Name: Domiciliary Brown Wolf
Description: Oh my! What sharp teeth this wolf has. But this particular big baby is more likely to lick you than bite you.

Name: Barkimedes' Puppy
Description: The grown spawn of the great Barkimedes and a settlement Mastiff; a forbidden romance for the ages.

Name: Dryad Grove Sapling
Description: From death comes new life. Even if this new life is an itty bitty tree.
Notes: A 0.5% drop rolled from PVE Arena Boss.

Name: Siren Queen’s Spear
Description: A powerful weapon once that once caused so much devastation, it now adorns the wall of your home.
Notes: A 0.5% drop rolled from PVE Arena Boss.

Name: Severed Spriggan’s Claw
Description: The severed hand of a defeated Spriggan. Starring at it gives you the urge to high-five it.
Notes: A 0.5% drop rolled from PVE Arena Boss.

Name: Crossed Arena Great Axes
Description: A pair of axes won from combat in the Arena. More suited for chopping limbs than chopping trees.
Notes: A 2.5% drop rolled for winners of the PVP Arena.

Name: Crossed Arena Hatchets
Description: Nimble throwing hatchets won from combat in the Arena. Better mounted on the wall than mounted in your head.
Notes: A 2.5% drop rolled for winners of the PVP Arena.

Name: Mounted Arena Saber
Description: A glistening sword mounted on deep, red wood. It wasn't clean at all when you earned it from combat in the Arena.
Notes: A 2.5% drop rolled for winners of the PVP Arena.

Name: Riches from the Arenas
Description: One thing is for sure, war and combat can be quite profitable. If you can survive it.
Notes: A 2.5% drop rolled for winners of the PVP Arena.

Name: Crossed Arena Swords
Description: Long and sturdy swords hard-fought and won from combat in the Arena. All the chips and dents from combat have been polished away.
Notes: A 2.5% drop rolled for winners of the PVP Arena.

Name: Mother's Love
Description: A decorative statue to honor all Mothers, past and present, infused with the spirit of Love and Motherhood.

Name: Snowcapped Bed
Description: A bed of hard ice and soft snow. Perfect for those who overheat in their sleep.

Name: Snowcapped Chair
Description: A chair carved from a single block of ice. Try not to sit on it with bare thighs lest you freeze right to the seat.

Name: Snowcapped Bookcase
Description: Thankfully the enchanted ice and snow never melts, so your scrolls and tomes will stay nice and dry on these shelves.

Name: Snowcapped Shelf
Description: A shelf carved of ice you can place on your wall. A 'cool' way to show off belongings in your house.

Name: Snowcapped Boar Sculpture
Description: A boorish boar balancing a bounding bearing upon a bright base.

Name: Snowcapped Rabbit Sculpture
Description: The hardest part about sculpting a rabbit from ice is getting the model to stay still.

Name: Snowcapped Stag Sculpture
Description: Mid-leap, and adorned with snow, this ice sculpture adds a dynamic factor to any room.

Name: Snowcapped Chandelier
Description: The icicles hanging from this chandelier never seem to melt, even with the bright lights within the lanterns.

Name: Snowcapped Lantern
Description: Despite the thick ice and snow, the cooling blue light within the lantern still shines unimpeded.

Name: Festive "Toy" Rabbit
Description: This rabbit isn't really a toy. It's just wearing a festive jacket, and is extra adorable for it.

Name: Snowcapped Nightstand
Description: For keeping your bedside drink cool overnight. Just hope it doesn't freeze while you sleep.

Name: Snowcapped Dining Table
Description: A sturdy table for a holiday feast. Now who's turn is it to cook this time?

Name: Snowcapped Yeti Sculpture
Description: With arms wide open to greet you for the holidays, this winter yeti will melt your heart faster than the ice it is made of.

Name: Wittl' Winter Whiskers
Description: This fluffy and posh companion adorned in festive garb happily celebrates with you that winter is finally here.

Name: Novelty Dancing Fish Dinner
Description: Surprise your guests with this fake fish feast. You'll have everyone hootin' and hollerin' to the music as this azoth-fueled novelty bass dances in the air.

Name: Summertime Marine Banner
Description: A lovely woven tapestry of a fish. The bright colors and patterns holds the feeling of summer all year round.

Name: Summertime Fish Grill
Description: Nothing says “summer in Aeternum” like a good ol’ fish grill. Fish included!

Name: Horned-Tooth Mandje - Medium Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Horned-Tooth Mandje you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. It was difficult to decide to make this trophy instead of an epic dish.

Name: Anchor - Large Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from an Anchor you pulled up during the Summer Medleyfaire. You wouldn't believe the strength it took to haul this out of the water.

Name: Albenaja - Large Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from an Albenaja you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. The pure white scales of this fish glisten like snow.

Name: Bass - Small Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Bass you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. This fish should have kept its big mouth shut if it didn't want to get caught.

Name: Abaia Serpe - Medium Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from an Abaia Serpe you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. While the vibrant colors are beautiful, the gaping mouth ruins the aesthetic.

Name: Bluefish - Medium Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Bluefish you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. One wonders if there are bluer fish out there, or is this the best you can get?

Name: Catfish - Medium Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Catfish you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. This thing doesn't look like a cat at all! The fish part, however, is spot on.

Name: Clam - Small Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Clam you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. Here's hoping the preservation process keeps the odors to a minimum.

Name: Cod - Medium Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Cod fish you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. A cold cod is a happy cod. Except this one. This one is dead.

Name: Dragon Fish - Small Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Dragon Fish you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. The two-toned scales do indeed remind one of a dragon, until you see the rest of it.

Name: Aquanaja - Large Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from an Aquanaja you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. Its slimy green frills make it near impossible to see amongst water vegetation.

Name: Electric Eel - Medium Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from an Electric Eel you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. It did zap you a few times while making this.

Name: Fish Sword - Large Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Fish Sword you pulled up during the Summer Medleyfaire. Not to be confused with a swordfish. Completely different.

Name: Flounder - Medium Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Flounder you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. This fish looks like someone took it apart and tried to put it back together, and failed.

Name: Frogfish - Small Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Frogfish you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. This fish wants to be it all. Orange. Fish. Frog. Hideous.

Name: Daemonaja - Large Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Daemonaja you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. This monster would be perfectly happy in the deepest, darkest parts of the sea.

Name: Hake - Medium Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Hake fish you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. The little fella looks like it's smiling, even though it wasn't happy to be caught.

Name: Halibut - Medium Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Halibut you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. It looks like someone lost their patience making this fish, said the hell with it, and called it a day.

Name: Fish Headed Hammer - Large Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Fish Headed Hammer you pulled up during the Summer Medleyfaire. It's got little eyes and fins and everything.

Name: Mackerel - Small Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Mackerel you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. A fish so oily, it's a wonder it didn't slip right off the hook.

Name: Madtom - Small Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Madtom you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. Too toxic to eat, but makes for interesting taxidermy.

Name: Mandje Mandje - Medium Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Mandje Mandje you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. The varying colors looks almost like a rainbow.

Name: Blue-Winged Serpe - Medium Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Blue-Winged Serpe you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. Looks more green than blue, but who's counting.

Name: Glowing Gnufish - Medium Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Glowing Gnufish you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. It uses its forearms to knock out prey so quickly, you blink and you miss it.

Name: Lava Barb - Large Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Lava Barb you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. Its stripes are so interesting and alluring. Until you get to the teeth part.

Name: Ray-Finned Barb - Large Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Ray - Finned Barb you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. It is a horror to behold to watch this thing eat. And yet, you can never look away.

Name: Egede Serpe - Medium Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from an Egede Serpe you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. The red and white stripes remind you of candy canes. But it doesn't taste like that at all!

Name: Oar - Large Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from an Oar you pulled up during the Summer Medleyfaire. Decent for whacking people in a pinch.

Name: Varanus Mandje - Medium Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Varanus Mandje you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. It likes to drag its tusks through the sediment to force out small prey.

Name: Paddlefish - Large Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Paddlefish you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. Its paddlin' days are over, but its modeling career has only just begun.

Name: Oyster - Small Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from an Oyster you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. You decided to keep the pearl in the oyster, if only to show it off.

Name: Pike - Large Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Pike you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. A fish that will eat almost anything that moves. Too bad its last meal was your lure.

Name: Piranha - Medium Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Piranha you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. Even though it is stuffed, it still looks like it wants to bite your fingers off.

Name: Salmon - Small Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Salmon you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. Most salmon is great for eating. Except this one. Don't eat this one.

Name: Sculpin - Medium Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Sculpin you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. It was a slow and delicate process making this and not getting stabbed.

Name: Seaweed - Small Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from some Seaweed you pulled up during the Summer Medleyfaire. Not your typical house-plant.

Name: Glowing Guardfish - Medium Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Glowing Guardfish you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. Based on how it looks, it isn't clear if this actually a fish or a crustacean. Maybe both?

Name: Aquatic Snail - Small Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from an Aquatic Snail you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. Preserving the shell was easy. Posing and preserving the snail part though…

Name: Snapper - Small Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Snapper you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. With its expression, name, and how red it is, you worry it will start yelling at you at any moment.

Name: Soggy Boot - Small Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Soggy Boot you pulled up during the Summer Medleyfaire. Whenever people look at this, they will wonder what ever happened to the other boot.

Name: Speartooth Shark - Large Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Speartooth Shark you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. The name is misleading. This shark has more than one tooth.

Name: Squid - Medium Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Squid you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. Its ink can be quite valuable, if you can manage to not collect it all over your shirt.

Name: Starfish - Small Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Starfish you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. The most popular of all the marine invertebrates.

Name: Stingray - Medium Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Stingray you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. This is if a bird wanted to be a fish, but became a leather kite instead.

Name: Sturgeon - Medium Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Sturgeon you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. If a fish could be a doctor, would that make them a sturgeon surgeon?

Name: Sunfish - Small Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Sunfish you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. Based on its expression, it doesn't have a very sunny disposition.

Name: Swordfish - Large Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Swordfish you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. Swordfish kisses must be very difficult. Even just rubbing noses is a hazard.

Name: Tadpole - Small Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Tadpole you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. If this is the size of the tadpole, how big is the frog?

Name: Blue-blooded Barb - Large Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Blue - blooded Barb you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. It must come from a long line of wealthy fish.

Name: Treasure Chest - Large Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Treasure Chest you pulled up during the Summer Medleyfaire. Who knows what could be inside.

Name: Trout - Small Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Trout you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. This trout must be shy. It is blushing all the way down to its tail.

Name: Perch - Small Memento
Description: A commemorative trophy you crafted from a Perch fish you caught during the Summer Medleyfaire. It is unknown how this fish got its name. It sure isn't from sitting in trees.

Name: Summertime Fish Windsock
Description: A charming fish windsock that swims in the air both inside or outside your home, no matter which way the wind blows, or even if it blows at all.

Name: Summertime Floating Wall Lantern
Description: A colorful paper lantern that floats and spins in the air. Hopefully it won't float away.

Name: Summertime Hanging Frogfish Light
Description: This lantern is so life-like. You could almost swear that fish was the real deal. Though, how did they get it to glow like that?

Name: Summertime Blue Spotlight
Description: A crude spotlight made from barrels and glass. Light up the night sky with cool blue lights of fishing waters.

Name: Summertime Orange Spotlight
Description: A spotlight cobbled together from spare wood. The glass and mirror lights the sky with the orange fires of the summer sun.

Name: Summertime Holiday Torch
Description: Festive torches made of reed and bamboo. A popular light source during the Summer Medley holiday.

Name: Summer Medley Beach Bunny
Description: Most rabbits do not care for water, and this one is no exception. But that won't stop it from wearing a super cute bathing suit and lounging in the sunshine.

Name: Turkulon Egg Seat
Description: One of Turkulon's giant eggs. They usually explode, but this one was a dud. But if you were to sit on it long enough, would it hatch?

Name: Docile Pumpklin
Description: A tamed pumpklin pup. It loves getting watered so much, it bursts into blooms every time.

Name: Turkuless, Disgruntled Fowl
Description: The true mastermind behind Turkulon, Feathered Avenger of Death. But with his creation defeated, it now begrudgingly lives with you and accepts your pathetic morsels.

Name: Tattered Varangian Standard
Description: A tattered flag of the ruthless Varangians, a chilling omen of their brutal conquests.

Name: Spriggan Flame Brazier
Description: A replica of the flame braziers constructed to help quell the Fury of the Spriggan.

Name: Cerulean Sheets Bunk Bed
Description: An ash wood bunk bed crafted by artisan hands. Curl up on the blue comfy comforter and sleep in as late as you like.

Name: Cherry Sheets Bunk Bed
Description: There's no moping in this maple wood bunk bed. The warm, red blankets lifts your spirits all the way to dream land.

Name: Grassy Sheets Bunk Bed
Description: An oak wood bunk bed built for two. (Except no one ever takes the top bunk.) So go solo and sleep easy on bright green sheets.

Name: Sunny Sheets Bunk Bed
Description: Dark mahogany wood. Bright yellow cloth. Bountiful binary bedding. A doubly delightful contrast sure to make anyone rest easy.

Name: Ash Full Bed
Description: Blue sheets and ash wood makes up this simple yet comfortable bed. However this bed isn't really full until you are napping in it.

Name: Maple Full Bed
Description: This maple wood bed was made with love. (Hence the red sheets.) But it wasn't made for lovin'. Only sleeping. One person at a time!

Name: Oak Full Bed
Description: The green sheets might look inviting, like bouncy spring grass. But don't be fooled. This oak bed not for jumping. It's for... other stuff...

Name: Mahogany Full Bed
Description: I couldn't possibly sleep in this bed. The yellow sheets are just so bright and happy. The mahogany wood too deep and dark. The mattress... too... soft... zzzZZZzz....

Name: Straw Pet Bed
Description: Your loyal companion deserves nothing less than the best in straw-based bedding.

Name: Ash Dining Chair
Description: The rugged elegance of this chair elevates any home's style from 'rustic' to 'rustic chic'.

Name: Maple Dining Chair
Description: This maple dining chair is warm and inviting, just like you. The iron back supports make it strong enough to support even the weariest back.

Name: Oak Dining Chair
Description: This mighty oak chair is bound in iron, for a sitting experience that's as strong as you are.

Name: Mahogany Dining Chair
Description: Nothing like rocking out at the dinner table in this mahogany dining chair.

Name: Ash Casual Chair
Description: Though it looks somewhat rickety, the ash wood in this chair makes it strong and flexible.

Name: Maple Casual Chair
Description: The resonant maple wood in this beautiful chair will inspire any musician who sits in it.

Name: Oak Casual Chair
Description: Strong, stately, and surprisingly comfortable. You can see yourself dictating your memoirs from this chair.

Name: Mahogany Casual Chair
Description: This beautifully crafted mahogany rocking chair is not only elegant, it also has great lumbar support.

Name: Ash Barstool
Description: This ash barstool will support you through the good times and the bad.

Name: Maple Barstool
Description: Many a festive night has passed in bars across Aeternum, shared by people sitting on stools like this. It'll be a big hit at your housewarming party.

Name: Oak Barstool
Description: They say the greatest ruler in Aeternum's history refused his golden throne, preferring instead to sit on a simple oak stool just like this one.

Name: Mahogany Barstool
Description: The dark, lustrous wood of this mahogany stool would pair wonderfully with a bold rug.

Name: Warm Iron Chandelier - Bright
Description: Made with extra bright-burning tallow candles, this chandelier is the perfect mix of utility and ambiance.

Name: Warm Iron Chandelier - Dim
Description: The light from this chandelier is universally flattering, and will make you even more good-looking than you already are.

Name: Cool Iron Chandelier - Bright
Description: The cool tones of this chandelier's light are intended to mimic daylight, to help get you through those long Aeternian winters.

Name: Cool Iron Chandelier - Dim
Description: Azoth threads woven through the wicks of these candles provide a subtle blue-ish glow, and are also said to cause vivid dreams.

Name: Warm Iron Lantern - Bright
Description: The strength of this lantern's light makes it difficult to use for nefarious purposes. However, it's very popular with home decorators.

Name: Warm Iron Lantern - Dim
Description: The soft, warm light of this lantern in your window will always guide you home.

Name: Cool Iron Lantern - Bright
Description: This lantern casts a clean, sharp light, like the sun reflecting off fresh snow.

Name: Cool Iron Lantern - Dim
Description: This lantern is perfect for sitting around and telling ghost stories late at night.

Name: Warm Iron Sconce - Bright
Description: Shines a warm, relaxing light into even the darkest corners of your home.

Name: Warm Iron Sconce - Dim
Description: For when you want light, but not a lot of it. Just the right amount.

Name: Cool Iron Sconce - Bright
Description: The cool light from this wall sconce helps you make calm, rational decisions. Popular with doctors and accountants.

Name: Cool Iron Sconce - Dim
Description: Do you consider yourself more of a winter person? Then this is the perfect wall sconce for you!

Name: Round Sunny Rug
Description: A yellow rug shaped like the sun. Make you feel warm and happy just looking at it.

Name: Curved Grassy Rug
Description: This cheerful green rug feels especially good on bare feet. It reminds you of spring grass.

Name: Oval Cerulean Rug
Description: The bright blue dye used in this rug was made with a mixture of azoth and oak tree bark. The color can't be exactly replicated anywhere else in the world.

Name: Rectangle Cherry Rug
Description: This cheery red rug is fully reversible. Unfortunately, the other side is also red.

Name: Ash Armoire
Description: Ash is also known as "firelight" wood, and gives off a wonderful long-burning heat due to its density. Not that you'd ever burn your beautiful ash armoire, of course.

Name: Maple Armoire
Description: If you shut yourself into this armoire on a quiet night, you might be able to hear the wood around you resonate with the music of the cosmos.

Name: Oak Armoire
Description: An immortal owner needs an immortal place to store their clothes. The oak armoire is sturdy enough to withstand the ravages of both time and small explosions.

Name: Mahogany Armoire
Description: Just because you're a settler doesn't mean you have to settle for less than the best. This mahogany armoire is proof of your exquisite taste.

Name: Ash Small Bookcase
Description: The top interior decorator in Aeternum adores the weathered look of this compact ash bookcase, making it a very popular piece.

Name: Maple Small Bookcase
Description: There's no finer place to store all your old sea maps and star charts. You won't be needing them here on Aeternum.

Name: Oak Small Bookcase
Description: This oak bookcase is perfect for displaying your favorite flowers, for a bright pop of color and a soothing fragrance.

Name: Mahogany Small Bookcase
Description: If you're going to go to the trouble of owning all these impressive books, you may as well display them in this impressive mahogany bookcase.

Name: Ash Large Bookcase
Description: No metal fasteners were used in the joinery of this ash bookcase. Its craftsmanship is second to none.

Name: Maple Large Bookcase
Description: The same wood that went into this bookcase is also used by luthiers to craft Aeternum's finest musical instruments.

Name: Oak Large Bookcase
Description: This bookcase is sturdy enough to hold all your hopes and dreams for the future.

Name: Mahogany Large Bookcase
Description: This bookcase of gleaming mahogany lends you an air of confidence when you stand in front of it. Try it out!

Name: Ash Chest of Drawers
Description: Just imagining all the things you could put in these tiny drawers fills you with a sense of excitement.

Name: Maple Chest of Drawers
Description: This maple chest of drawers will keep your collection safe and sound. What collection? Any collection!

Name: Oak Chest of Drawers
Description: What's inside the drawers isn't important. What really matters is that you did your best.

Name: Mahogany Chest of Drawers
Description: This chest has four drawers, one for each of the major accessory groups: capes, half-capes, falconry gloves, and socks.

Name: Ash Cabinet
Description: Some people claim that clothes kept in this ash wood cabinet will never go out of fashion.

Name: Maple Cabinet
Description: There is a custom on Aeternum that a young woodsman must use his own two hands to make a cabinet out of the first tree he ever fells.

Name: Oak Cabinet
Description: You can't just hide your secrets in any old cabinet. There's a saying on Aeternum: 'oak never tells'.

Name: Mahogany Cabinet
Description: The cubbyholes in this mahogany cabinet are the perfect place to store your various medals and commendations.

Name: Sewing Accessories
Description: Sewing is one of the most practical skills any adventurer can have. No one else is going to mend your pants for you.

Name: Floral Design Accessories
Description: Life on Aeternum can be stressful. Flower arrangement is a healthy way to unwind after a day full of dying.

Name: Desk Accessories
Description: You can write about whatever you want with this desk set. It's here to support you and your literary dreams.

Name: Fireplace Poker Set
Description: Many a retired adventurer has spent their golden years poking at the fire and thinking of the past.

Name: Fireplace Accessories
Description: A bellows for the optimists. A bucket of water for the realists.

Name: Fireplace Books
Description: What better place to store your precious books than near an open flame?

Name: Hanging Basket of Flowers
Description: The scent of these cheerful yellow flowers is strongest at solar noon, earning them the nickname 'sunbathers'. On the summer solstice, they can be smelled from up to fifty yards away.

Name: Pot of Winter Flowers
Description: An arrangement of winter blooms. The red berries of the firethorn are said to ease homesickness when eaten. They are a traditional welcoming gift for newcomers to Aeternum.

Name: Pot of Blue Flowers
Description: Delphinium flower cultivation is a popular pastime on Aeternum, and garden competitions can be cutthroat. The plant contains deadly alkaloids, and "accidental" poisonings occur frequently.

Name: Pot of Pink Flowers
Description: A colorful display of aster and wormwood that soothes a tired soul.

Name: Wooden Wheelbarrow
Description: A wheelbarrow is a marvelous invention. Now you no longer have to transport manure with your bare hands.

Name: Wheelbarrow of Garden Supplies
Description: A good garden takes sweat to plant and time to grow. Your trusty wheelbarrow will be with you every step of the way.

Name: Colorful Wind Chimes
Description: When the wind blows from the south, the colorful ribbons and melody reminds you of your childhood. Ring any bells?

Name: Robust Wind Chimes
Description: It takes a pretty stiff wind to rattle these chunky copper chimes. But when they chime, it is a sound to behold.

Name: "Bear in Meadow" Painting
Description: A serene oil painting in an ash wood frame. No one is quite sure how the artist got the bear in this painting to stand still for six hours.

Name: "Beyond the Gate" Painting
Description: A haunting watercolor painting in a maple wood frame. It is so rich with atmosphere that the viewer can almost feel the chilly mist on their skin.

Name: "Mountain Dawn" Painting
Description: A painting that captures the essence of an Aeternian sunrise within a fine oak frame. The painter nearly drove herself mad trying to capture the passing of autumn with the coming of winter.

Name: "Spring River" Painting
Description: It is hard to tell which is nicer; the oil painting of a scenic river, or the carved and polish mahogany frame it rests within.

Name: Wooden Dishes
Description: Simple dishes, carved from simple wood, for simple meals. What could be more simple?

Name: Stacked Dishes
Description: A good host always has enough plates to make sure that no one leaves hungry.

Name: Dirty Dishes
Description: Washing the dishes can be a risky proposition when you have to go down to the river to do it. But the mallet does provide some protection.

Name: Well-Loved Dishes
Description: The wear and tear on these dishes is a testament to countless meals savored to the last bite.

Name: Cauldron Cooking Set
Description: In the Old World, a good cauldron was often passed down through the generations. Here in Aeternum, nothing gets passed down.

Name: Campfire Cooking Set
Description: Cooking is a very important survival skill in Aeternum. Anyone who has ever tried to eat raw boar meat will understand why.

Name: Sturdy Cooking Set
Description: You've gained mastery over fire. Prove your dominance by using it to cook a delicious meal.

Name: Fresh Flowers Assembly
Description: A sprinkle of lemon juice will keep your flowers looking as fresh as the day you cut them.

Name: Meal Prep Set
Description: You're ready to create a culinary masterpiece. Now all you need is the food.

Name: Cerulean Place Setting
Description: Is this the aftermath of a meal, or the beforemath? (Beforemath is a common word in Aeternum.)

Name: Cherry Place Setting
Description: This tableware is almost too pretty to use, unless you're hungry, and the bright red placemat makes you real hungry for fresh fruit.

Name: Grassy Place Setting
Description: You might just lose sight of your meal if you were to have a picnic on the grass, that is, if the ants don't get to it first.

Name: Sunny Place Setting
Description: Every meal you eat makes you feel a bit happier, a bit brighter when you use this place setting. I wonder why?

Name: Cerulean Drape
Description: A thick, blue drape to block the light from a window. Perfect for those who like to sleep until noon.

Name: Cherry Drape
Description: You won't feel dreary with this delightfully dapper drape. The bright red reminds you of fresh fruit.

Name: Grassy Drape
Description: If you don't want to look out a window at the green rolling hills, you can look at this drape instead, with its green rolling fabric.

Name: Sunny Drape
Description: You can have a bright outlook with this drape, even if you can't look out a window through it.

Name: Cerulean Valance
Description: A lovely blue colored fabric hanging loosely. For those who want all the style of a curtain with none of the utility.

Name: Cherry Valance
Description: Think of this bright red fabric like a window hat. It is pretty, and does very little to keep the light out.

Name: Grassy Valance
Description: Bring the outdoors in with some grassy green fabric. Drapery never looked so good.

Name: Sunny Valance
Description: Add some lovely color with this happy fabric. You can hang it above your windows, your door, your bed. Any wall you like!

Name: Cerulean Curtains
Description: The sky's the limit with these blue sky drapes. It's the next best thing to being outside.

Name: Cherry Curtains
Description: Frame your window with style. And nothing says 'style' like these cherry colored drapes. They really make the room pop.

Name: Grassy Curtains
Description: Bring the spirit of the forest inside with these long green drapes. Their tallness reminds you of trees.

Name: Sunny Curtains
Description: You won't be able to tell where the window stops and these curtains begin on a sunny day.

Name: Summertime Wreath
Description: This exuberant wreath uses dried flowers, so you can get that summertime feel even in the dead of winter.

Name: Delphinium Wreath
Description: Hanging a wreath of delphiniums on your door or in your window means that you're ready for visitors. Hope the place is clean!

Name: Ash Dresser
Description: This single-source dresser was crafted from the wood of one ash tree, which had lived a long, full life with no regrets.

Name: Maple Dresser
Description: To make a maple dresser of this quality, the artisan must completely clear their mind of all thoughts. Then, they say, the dresser makes itself.

Name: Oak Dresser
Description: Oak wood is associated with the king of gods in many mythic traditions. Your socks and underwear deserve nothing less.

Name: Mahogany Dresser
Description: This dresser has been burnished with a rich oil, to bring out the grain of the wood. Your unmentionables will be stored in luxury.

Name: Ash Wall Shelf
Description: The flexible joints of this ash shelf can support the heaviest of collectible figurines.

Name: Maple Wall Shelf
Description: This maple shelf calls out for something soft and comforting, like your favorite stuffed animal.

Name: Oak Wall Shelf
Description: Oak trees are the most likely to be hit by lightning. Luckily, this shelf is specially insulated.

Name: Mahogany Wall Shelf
Description: This shelf is perfect for displaying your most expensive violin. You have one of those, right?

Name: Iron Settler's Stove
Description: This stove takes time to heat up, but will stay warm long after the fire burns down.

Name: Steel Settler's Stove
Description: This handsome stove is rust-resistant and waterproof up to a depth of 30 feet.

Name: Starmetal Settler's Stove
Description: This stove gives off heat even when there's no fuel inside. Unsettling, but saves on heating costs.

Name: Orichalcum Settler's Stove
Description: In the Old World, orichalcum was so rare that it was almost mythical. Here on Aeternum, it makes for a very shiny stove.

Name: Hope Storage Chest
Description:
A chest that grants access to your storage, and increases your storage by {[HouseItems.House_HousingItem_Storage_T3_Settler.StorageBonus / 10]} weight when placed in your home. 
Made with the hope for a long, happy life.

Name: Ash End Table
Description: The energy in your house seems so much lighter, now that you have this ash end table.

Name: Maple End Table
Description: No matter what you keep next to your bed, this maple end table will not judge you.

Name: Oak End Table
Description: This oak end table is strong enough to hold all your hardest-hitting books and periodicals.

Name: Mahogany End Table
Description: When you wake up screaming in the night, the reassuring presence of mahogany bedside table will help calm you.

Name: Picnic Table
Description: This weather-beaten picnic table has seen many birthday parties in its day.

Name: Ash Desk
Description: You are a popular person with many friends. Keep in touch with all of them by writing letters at this attractive ash desk.

Name: Maple Desk
Description: Writing at this desk could inspire a symphony. All you have to do is close your eyes and listen.

Name: Oak Desk
Description: When houseguests see this mighty oak desk, they'll say, "Wow. This desk must belong to a very important person." That person is you.

Name: Mahogany Desk
Description: Look left. Look right. None of your neighbors have more exquisite taste in desks than you do.

Name: Ash Small Table
Description: When you're not hungry enough for a full meal, this snack-sized ash dining table is just right.

Name: Maple Small Table
Description: This sturdy table is perfect for use as a workbench. Unleash your creative side!

Name: Oak Small Table
Description: This oak table may be small, but it holds memories of being the mightiest tree in the forest.

Name: Mahogany Small Table
Description: No matter what you put on this mahogany table, it will be exactly the right choice.

Name: Ash Large Table
Description: Ash wood has natural protective and healing properties. You'll never get indigestion from food eaten off this table.

Name: Maple Large Table
Description: Just think of the warm, nourishing meals you and your loved ones will eat off this table.

Name: Oak Large Table
Description: A dining table needs to be sturdy. This oak table can hold a feast and a half without even creaking.

Name: Mahogany Large Table
Description: The rich red hue of this magnificent table whispers 'luxury'. Not too much; just enough.

Name: Maritime Velvet Captain's Bed
Description: Blue, like the endless ocean. Velvet, like your singing voice.

Name: Sea Foam Velvet Captain's Bed
Description: This is the bed a mermaid queen would sleep in, if mermaids ever slept.

Name: Bloody Velvet Captain's Bed
Description: A red velvet bed, the color of battle. Classic pirate king vibes.

Name: Gothic Velvet Captain's Bed
Description: Sometimes you lie awake at night, thinking about death, but in a way that makes you seem sensitive and interesting to others.

Name: Sailor's Hammock
Description: Perfect to relax in. Too bad it is way too easy to fall out of. Better not risk it.

Name: Maritime Velvet Armchair
Description: Sit back. Relax. It's good to be the Captain.

Name: Sea Foam Velvet Armchair
Description: The soothing color will help keep you calm while making life-or-death decisions.

Name: Bloody Velvet Armchair
Description: A chair fit for a king. Stolen from a king, in fact.

Name: Gothic Velvet Armchair
Description: You've read that both purple and velvet are signs of royalty, making this chair twice as majestic.

Name: Maritime Velvet Dining Chair
Description: The decorative turned legs can be used as impromptu weapons in a pinch.

Name: Sea Foam Velvet Dining Chair
Description: Made with the bronzed skull of the last person to correct your table manners.

Name: Bloody Velvet Dining Chair
Description: Mark your spot at the head of the table with this sumptuous gilded chair.

Name: Gothic Velvet Dining Chair
