Description: This chair is the color of the darkened sky before a hurricane.

Name: Maritime Velvet Footstool
Description: You can feel the tension drain out of your aching bones as soon as you sit down on the plush velvet.

Name: Sea Foam Velvet Footstool
Description: The pale light green of this stool makes you feel like you are practically floating the moment you place your tuchus on it.

Name: Bloody Velvet Footstool
Description: This red velvet ottoman is so soft and cushy. The gilded feet add an extra dash of panache.

Name: Gothic Velvet Footstool
Description: A stool this comfortable almost feels wrong. Almost.

Name: Skull Candleholder
Description: Something very dark and very bright at the same time.

Name: Hard-Working Helm Chandelier
Description: This wheel once guided a mighty ship. Now, it'll help guide you through the dark.

Name: Salt-stripped Helm Chandelier
Description: After a long, hard life at sea, this ship's wheel is exploring other career options.

Name: Well-polished Helm Chandelier
Description: Salvaged from a shipwreck and expertly restored by a master craftsman.

Name: Black-lacquered Helm Chandelier
Description: This wheel once belonged to the ship of the best-dressed pirate crew in the South Seas.

Name: Silver Candelabra
Description: Miraculously untarnished despite decades spent underwater.

Name: Bronze Candelabra
Description: The patina on this well-preserved candelabra gives away its immense age.

Name: Gold Candelabra
Description: A body washed up onshore with this solid gold candelabra strapped to its back. Unfortunately, it did not make a good flotation device.

Name: Brass Candelabra
Description: This candelabra was recovered from a French shipwreck. Its exquisite detail was revealed once the barnacles were scrubbed off.

Name: Captain Quicksilver's Lamp, Silver Replica
Description: The craze for Quicksilver lamps lasted only a few years. This late-model silver lamp was sold at a deep discount, as most pirates had moved on to the next big thing.

Name: Captain Quicksilver's Lamp, Bronze Replica
Description: Captain Quicksilver's Lamp sparked a craze, and replicas like this one soon became the most-requested item in the furniture workshops of Tortuga.

Name: Captain Quicksilver's Lamp, Gold Replica
Description: Soon, anyone who was anyone in the pirating world had to have a Quicksilver lamp. This solid gold example was the subject of one fierce bidding war and two subsequent assassinations.

Name: Captain Quicksilver's Lamp, Original
Description: The final request of infamous pirate James 'Quicksilver' Forten was that his skull be turned into a wall lamp.

Name: Reflector Lamp
Description: The clever use of reflection produces twice the light.

Name: Pirate Nightlight
Description: Young pirates who use this nightlight no longer fear the dark. There are so many other things to fear instead.

Name: Hard-Working Scrolled Armoire
Description: This armoire has the perfect balance of craftsmanship, practicality, and skulls.

Name: Salt-stripped Scrolled Armoire
Description: Every crack in the wood of this armoire tells a story of the high seas.

Name: Well-polished Scrolled Armoire
Description: A savvy captain knows: take care of your things, and they'll take care of you.

Name: Black-lacquered Scrolled Armoire
Description: A popular fairytale claims that Bluebeard told his new wife to never, ever, open this armoire.

Name: Captain's Bath
Description: Only the captain is allowed to indulge in that rarest of pirate luxuries - a bath.

Name: Hard-Working Half-Barrel Table
Description: Cleverly repurposed from a barrel, this watertight table could serve as a boat for a very small person.

Name: Salt-stripped Half-Barrel Table
Description: Is that a skull on that shelf? Do you bring a skull to bed? Don't answer that question.

Name: Well-polished Half-Barrel Table
Description: So richly burnished, you can hardly tell it used to be a humble barrel.

Name: Black-lacquered Half-Barrel Table
Description: The rum in this barrel was aged for twelve years before the barrel found new life as a table. Even now, the sweet smell lingers.

Name: Hard-Working Low Bookcase
Description: A good library is a great comfort to a sleepless captain on those long, lonely nights at sea.

Name: Salt-stripped Low Bookcase
Description: The finish might been washed off this bookcase by the hard salt sea, but it still holds just as much knowledge as ever.

Name: Well-polished Low Bookcase
Description: A pirate must be well-read, if he wishes to move undetected in high society.

Name: Black-lacquered Low Bookcase
Description: The bookcase once housed the personal library of the child King. He enjoyed books with lots of pictures.

Name: Hard-Working Tall Bookcase
Description: This multifunctional piece of furniture serves as a bookcase, a writing desk, and a dresser. So practical!

Name: Salt-stripped Tall Bookcase
Description: The wood is worn, but the brass hardware looks brand new. Was this bookcase deliberately roughed up?

Name: Well-polished Tall Bookcase
Description: Crafted with love in a Parisian workshop, generations ago.

Name: Black-lacquered Tall Bookcase
Description: The history behind this antique bookcase would make any museum curator green with envy.

Name: Hard-Working Short Dresser
Description: A safe and stylish place to store your finery.

Name: Salt-stripped Short Dresser
Description: The little skull-shaped drawer-pulls on this dresser are surprisingly charming.

Name: Well-polished Short Dresser
Description: Wow. Even the underside of this dresser is polished to a mirror finish.

Name: Black-lacquered Short Dresser
Description: The main thing that separates a good pirate captain from a legendary one is good costume design. This dresser can help with that.

Name: Hard-Working Tall Dresser
Description: Look at all those drawers. You'll be able to store all your billowing silk shirts in here.

Name: Salt-stripped Tall Dresser
Description: You might need a ladder to reach those top drawers. That's where you'll hide the good stuff.

Name: Well-polished Tall Dresser
Description: Even if you've got nothing to wear but rags, you need a nice place to put them.

Name: Black-lacquered Tall Dresser
Description: On windy nights, you can hear the skulls whisper fashion tips to one another. Or was that just a dream?

Name: Pirate Anchor
Description: A fond remembrance of a ship blown to bits long ago.

Name: Imitation Bone Wreath
Description: Despite its realistic appearance, this bone wreath was actually whittled from basswood.

Name: Storage Cage
Description: Why deal with shelving when you have a perfectly good ceiling cage to store your extra stuff.

Name: Iron Cannonballs
Description: These cannonballs never saw action in battle.

Name: Short Iron Chain
Description: You never know what kind of thing you might need to hang from your ceiling.

Name: Long Iron Chain
Description: You could use it as a swing, if you have really good balance.

Name: Extra Long Iron Chain
Description: After a life at sea, many pirates can't get to sleep without the soothing rattle of iron chains.

Name: Maritime Posh Valance
Description: The view out the window can only be enhanced by hanging this blue velvet fabric above it.

Name: Sea Foam Posh Valance
Description: Not enough velvet in your house? Here's an easy and fabulous fix.

Name: Bloody Posh Valance
Description: This red velvet valance gives a sumptuous look to any captain's window.

Name: Gothic Posh Valance
Description: This velvet valance is much too elegant to be useful.

Name: Maritime Posh Curtains
Description: These curtains have the maximum number of tassels allowed by Aeternian law.

Name: Sea Foam Posh Curtains
Description: Keeps your cabin warm and cozy on cold nights.

Name: Bloody Posh Curtains
Description: These curtains are so lovely, you won't even want to look out the window.

Name: Gothic Posh Curtains
Description: The captain is the only person on the ship allowed to sleep in. These heavy velvet curtains will block out every trace of early morning sun.

Name: Maritime Ragged Curtains
Description: These curtains are somehow both opulent and threadbare at the same time.

Name: Sea Foam Ragged Curtains
Description: No need to draw these curtains. They'll let the daylight through either way.

Name: Bloody Ragged Curtains
Description: These curtains might have been the height of luxury...once.

Name: Gothic Ragged Curtains
Description: For when there is darkness in your soul, but not too much.

Name: Grog Crate
Description: A crate of grog bottles. It might not be fancy, but at least there's a lot of it.

Name: Canteen Set
Description: Technically, this canteen is meant to be used for water.

Name: Small Beer Set
Description: Beer provides vital nutrition and calories to sailors on long voyages. It often contains less than 1% alcohol.

Name: Moderate Drinking Set
Description: This drinking set is used to imbibe alcohol in moderation, and in accordance with all local laws and statutes.

Name: Old World Globe
Description: You'll never see the world outside Aeternum again. But at least you can look at this globe.

Name: Pirate Jewel Box
Description: When your ship is being pursued by howling ghosts, you can look at this loot and know that it was all worth it.

Name: Ottoman Tea Set
Description: This beautiful mixed-metal tea set was crafted in one of the finest workshops in Damascus.

Name: Map of Aeternum
Description: This map of Aeternum is beautiful, but unfinished. There's still much left to discover.

Name: Tightly Furled Map
Description: A rolled-up map holds infinite possibilities.

Name: Captain's Writing Set
Description: Nothing can be more final than a threatening letter to your enemies. Except, perhaps, how your enemies might respond to said letter.

Name: Cartographer's Tools
Description: These tools once belonged to the most talented cartographer who ever sailed the Mediterranean Sea.

Name: Oar-nament
Description: Even in the golden age of sailing, sometimes you've got no choice but to row.

Name: "The Amaranta" Painting
Description: A melancholy painting in a silver and burlwood frame. The proud captain of this Spanish galleon never got around to getting her portrait painted while she was still in one piece.

Name: "Journey's End" Painting
Description: A beatific painting in an arched silver frame. To a pirate, there's no sight more beautiful than a port that he had given up hope of ever reaching.

Name: "Flying Dutchman" Painting
Description: A timeworn painting in an oval frame. After lights out, sailors used to trade whispered stories about ghost ships like the one in this painting.

Name: Maritime Place Setting
Description: The tranquil color encourages your guests to linger over dessert.

Name: Sea Foam Place Setting
Description: Yes, it's hard to get food stains out of velvet. But this is a matter of style.

Name: Bloody Place Setting
Description: You treat your dinner guests with respect, but also gently remind them that you can have them killed at any time.

Name: Gothic Place Setting
Description: With this place setting, any meal becomes a kingly feast.

Name: Ship's Cookware
Description: A sturdy set of iron cookware is worth its weight in stolen gemstones.

Name: Pirate Rigging
Description: These ropes are so beautifully rigged, they could bring an old sailor to tears.

Name: Fishing Net Decoration
Description: The fibers of this old fishing net remember the struggle of every fish it ever caught.

Name: Pirate Rum Crate
Description: An ingenious pirate managed to smuggle a whole shipment of fine cognac out of France by disguising it in these humble rum bottles.

Name: Clouded Glass Jug
Description: The very last bottle of this particular vintage left in the world.

Name: Scholarly Scroll
Description: A pirate scholar's treatise on the great Stormwall of Aeternum.

Name: Letter of Marque
Description: An old letter of marque - once a free pass to pillage and terrorize, now just a fond memento.

Name: Pirate Sign
Description: Seeing this sign outside a tavern door lets you know that you're in for a fun and wholesome time.

Name: Skull With Fancy Hat
Description: This proud pirate swore he'd rather die than be parted from his beloved hat.

Name: Ship Wheel Swords Display
Description: These swords aren't just for show. They're kept meticulously polished and sharpened in case of a dueling emergency.

Name: Brass Telescope
Description: This state-of-the-art brass telescope is a great comfort for former sailors who once used the stars to navigate the open sea.

Name: Freshwater Barrel
Description: Filled with sweet water transported from the fresh glacier brooks of northern Aeternum.

Name: Pirate Washtub
Description: One benefit of being a landlubber: clothes cleaned in fresh water cause way less chafing.

Name: Pirate Weapon Arrangement
Description: A selection of fine weapons, taken off the bodies of adversaries who made the mistake of fighting fair.

Name: Flintlock Pistols
Description: These beautiful flintlock pistols have a walnut stock and a top firing rate of three rounds per minute.

Name: Pirate Crew Keg
Description: This keg is proof that you throw the best parties in town. The whole crew is invited!

Name: Hard-Working Galley Shelf
Description: This shelf holds everything a well-stocked galley needs.

Name: Salt-stripped Galley Shelf
Description: You can store your balsamic vinegar on this shelf without worrying about ruining the finish.

Name: Well-polished Galley Shelf
Description: This shelf might be a practical piece of furniture, but that doesn't mean it doesn't deserve fancy gold scrollwork.

Name: Black-lacquered Galley Shelf
Description: A cheeky combination of luxury and coziness that's sure to turn heads.

Name: Copper Water Pump
Description: The ingenious copper mechanism atop this sink actually heats the water as you pump it! Incredible!

Name: Ornate Cast-Iron Stove
Description: The iron will keep your vittles hot for a long, long time.

Name: Ornate Copper Stove
Description: If copper was good enough for the ancient Romans, it's good enough for you.

Name: Ornate Bronze Stove
Description: This stove was a special order from a pirate captain who loved to cook.

Name: Ornate Gold Stove
Description: This stove proves that you have money to burn.

Name: Curved Maritime Rug
Description: Often placed in a lady's cabin, because a woman's bare feet touching the wood of the ship was considered bad luck.

Name: Round Sea Foam Rug
Description: The beautiful color is worth the effort it takes to keep it clean.

Name: Crescent Bloody Rug
Description: The rich red color of this rug hides bloodstains extremely well.

Name: Oval Gothic Rug
Description: Bewitchingly soft on your bare toes.

Name: Booty Storage Chest
Description:
A chest that grants access to your storage, and increases your storage by {[HouseItems.House_HousingItem_Storage_T3_Pirate.StorageBonus / 10]} weight when placed in your home. 
The kind of chest every pirate dreams of digging up.

Name: Short Barrel Countertop
Description: With convenient built-in barrel storage!

Name: Long Barrel Countertop
Description: This counter is perfect for counting your treasure. The mallet is for anyone who tries to interrupt you.

Name: Hard-Working Scrolled Desk
Description: This desk is just for fun. Everyone knows that the best part of being a pirate is - no paperwork.

Name: Salt-stripped Scrolled Desk
Description: Watch out for splinters in your writing hand.

Name: Well-polished Scrolled Desk
Description: This desk is perfect for writing poetry and ransom notes.

Name: Black-lacquered Scrolled Desk
Description: A legendary pirate queen once wrote letters to her many lovers at this desk.

Name: Hard-Working Vanity Table
Description: It's important to look your best while raining terror down on your enemies.

Name: Salt-stripped Vanity Table
Description: Place this handsome vanity table near your front door, to make sure your hat looks good before you leave.

Name: Well-polished Vanity Table
Description: You wake in a cold sweat. There's someone in the room! Wait, no... it's just your reflection in this fine vanity mirror.

Name: Black-lacquered Vanity Table
Description: This gilded vanity was a custom order from a Dutch workshop that specializes in pirate décor.

Name: Pirate Keg Kitchen Island
Description: Imagine how many off-key sea shanties this double keg countertop has heard.

Name: Hard-Working Dining Table
Description: A table for those with great taste and a big appetite for culinary adventure.

Name: Salt-stripped Dining Table
Description: The bronze skulls, ever-present reminders of death, help you truly savor your meal as if it were your last.

Name: Well-polished Dining Table
Description: Being invited to dine at the Captain's table is a great honor for a humble pirate.

Name: Black-lacquered Dining Table
Description: Imagine how much champagne and caviar this table could hold. (And yet somehow, still not enough.)

Name: Hard-Working Small Table
Description: Perfect for a small, tight-knit crew.

Name: Salt-stripped Small Table
Description: This style of table is becoming increasingly popular in Aeternum, even among landlubbers.

Name: Well-polished Small Table
Description: Elegant, yet space-efficient. Captain approved.

Name: Black-lacquered Small Table
Description: Contains a hidden compartment for snacks. Very expensive snacks!

Name: Teak Carved Canopy Bed
Description: Every morning, you'll wake from sleep, see this bed, and remember instantly that you've made it in life.

Name: Ebony Carved Canopy Bed
Description: The red silk sheets will draw joy, luck, and happiness to your home.

Name: Rosewood Carved Canopy Bed
Description: The mix of cool teal silks and warm red woods has an interesting affect in making you feel both alert, yet relaxed.

Name: Jade Carved Canopy Bed
Description: A bed extravagantly carved from one block of pure jade. Jade is said to represent good health and long life…in bed.

Name: Goldenrod Silk Daybed
Description: The rich warm hue of the silk cushions will give you the energy you need to curl up and finish that novel you're reading.

Name: Ruby Silk Daybed
Description: The contrast between the red silk and the black wood is especially striking.

Name: Turquoise Silk Daybed
Description: Such a tranquil color. What a perfect place for a nap.

Name: White Gold Silk Daybed
Description: The craftsmanship is exquisite, even if the carved jade is a bit cold on your back.

Name: Carved Teak Armchair
Description: The curves of this chair are both architectural and ergonomical.

Name: Carved Ebony Armchair
Description: A chair like this almost makes you regret your immortality, just so you could have passed it down to your children.

Name: Carved Rosewood Armchair
Description: The hue of the wood is so rich and warm, it's almost a shame to cover it up with your butt.

Name: Carved Jade Armchair
Description: Sitting in this luminous jade chair is said to open several chakras at once.

Name: Graceful Teak Chair
Description: The slim legs of this chair are much sturdier than they look.

Name: Graceful Ebony Chair
Description: This antique chair was crafted centuries ago, in a legendary imperial workshop.

Name: Graceful Rosewood Chair
Description: The abalone seat of this chair has a strange, beautiful luminosity.

Name: Graceful Jade Chair
Description: The combination of jade and abalone will keep you cool on even the hottest summer days.

Name: Carved Teak Stool
Description: For a stool, this piece offers a surprising amount of lounging space.

Name: Carved Ebony Stool
Description: Rub a bit of walnut oil into this well-loved antique to bring out its original shine.

Name: Carved Rosewood Stool
Description: Sitting on this rich red stool will force you to improve your posture.

Name: Carved Jade Stool
Description: Sitting on this stool feels like sitting at the bottom of a tranquil, sun-dappled pond.

Name: Teak Apothecary Cabinet
Description: Keep your wits sharp by trying to remember what you put in all these drawers.

Name: Ebony Apothecary Cabinet
Description: In addition to all the normal drawers, this armoire also contains at least one secret drawer.

Name: Rosewood Apothecary Cabinet
Description: With this fine cabinet in your house, don't be surprised if your neighbors start coming to you for medical advice.

Name: Jade Apothecary Cabinet
Description: Ingredients kept in these jade drawers somehow stay fresh longer.

Name: Large Teak Bookcase
Description: The brass hardware on this antique bookcase is still in incredible condition.

Name: Large Ebony Bookcase
Description: This multi-level case is perfect for displaying all your curiosities.

Name: Large Rosewood Bookcase
Description: True interior design is not about the things you put on the shelves, but about the space you leave between them.

Name: Large Jade Bookcase
Description: No need to buy fancy first editions. You could put any book on this shelf, and it would still look stunning.

Name: Narrow Teak Bookcase
Description: Each shelf has a handy railing so your books won't fall off the back.

Name: Narrow Ebony Bookcase
Description: This bookcase was made before books were even invented.

Name: Narrow Rosewood Bookcase
Description: Books with upsetting covers can go in the drawers.

Name: Narrow Jade Bookcase
Description: You'll retain 10% more information from books stored in a jade bookcase.

Name: Painted Teak Chest
Description: This beautiful teak chest is equally good at storing silks and snacks.

Name: Painted Ebony Chest
Description: If you put your ear to this chest, you might hear the echoes of many years of domestic bliss.

Name: Painted Rosewood Chest
Description: The dragons painted on the doors of this chest will protect its contents from the outside world.

Name: Painted Jade Chest
Description: The artist developed a special type of paint that adheres to jade without damaging it.

Name: Teak Weapon Rack
Description: Finally, a convenient way to organize all those weapons you've got lying around.

Name: Ebony Weapon Rack
Description: For extra peace of mind, keep this handy weapon rack right next to your bed.

Name: Rosewood Weapon Rack
Description: This beautiful weapon rack comes with a scratch-resistant varnish. Protects the wood, and your weapons.

Name: Jade Weapon Rack
Description: Are those the ancient spears of legend? They must be, to earn a place on this incredible weapon rack.

Name: Hanging Wicker Bowls
Description: These bowls dry super fast when you suspend them from the ceiling.

Name: Hanging Herb Garden
Description: This multi-tier planter is perfect for growing herbs and spices.

Name: Hanging Plant Nursery
Description: The shoots and cuttings in these planters will grow big and strong under your care.

Name: Hanging Bonsai
Description: You've found that the drainage offered by this suspended shelf is perfect for your treasured bonsai.

Name: Green Clay Pot
Description: The cheerful green color seems to keep the contents fresher.

Name: Red Clay Pot
Description: The cork stopper makes this pot useful for long-term storage.

Name: Natural Clay Amphora
Description: This jar is tough enough to stand up to daily use. Usually filled with wine, beer, or oil.

Name: Red Clay Amphora
Description: Sealed on top to prevent spillage and evaporation.

Name: Living Bamboo Planter
Description: These bamboo shoots are growing so well, they'll soon need a bigger planter.

Name: Bamboo Display Vase
Description: Which is more exquisite, the bamboo or the vase? Ah, that's a philosophical question.

Name: Cut Bamboo Storage Pot
Description: A no-nonsense clay pot, to store your no-nonsense bamboo poles.

Name: Crowded Armory Rack
Description: This is the armory rack of a person who has had many, many adventures.

Name: Short Green Porcelain Vase
Description: The gemstone luster of this planter is so beautiful, it doesn't even need a plant.

Name: Short Red Porcelain Vase
Description: This exquisite planter features a crimson overglaze with a design stenciled in silver leaf, in the traditional style.

Name: Short Black Porcelain Vase
Description: The pattern on this planter is reminiscent of luxurious brocade cloth.

Name: Short Cream Porcelain Vase
Description: The subtle shine of the gold foil on the cream-colored background invites a longer look.

Name: Short White Porcelain Vase
Description: This vibrant blue pigment is hard to source these days. This planter is truly something special.

Name: Iron Wok Set
Description: A wok is an incredibly versatile piece of cookware. You can make almost anything in it.

Name: Unwashed China
Description: These delicate dishes will be even more beautiful when they're clean.

Name: Dumpling Steamer Set
Description: These bamboo baskets will serve up plump, glistening, perfectly-steamed dumplings.

Name: Tea and Snacks China Set
Description: Graciously host an afternoon tea party, or a midnight cake party. Anytime is the right time with this refined tea set.

Name: Tea Ceremony Set
Description: A traditional tea ceremony is a chance to unwind, savor the moment, and contemplate the beautiful transience of life.

Name: Goldfish in Porcelain Bowl
Description: Feel free to admire, but watch out; this feisty goldfish loves to splash anyone who comes in range.

Name: Winter Flower Arrangement
Description: The fruits of the fall harvest will keep your spirits up during the long, cold Aeternian winter.

Name: Fusion Flower Arrangement
Description: A good flower arrangement invokes surprise and delight. This contrast of the maidenhair and baby's breath is a prime example.

Name: Poignant Flower Arrangement
Description: Both the aster and artemesia flowers are named after ancient goddesses.

Name: Goldenrod Place Setting
Description: A beautiful place setting increases anticipation for the coming meal.

Name: Ruby Place Setting
Description: In Aeternum, the soup is usually served after the main course.

Name: Turquoise Place Setting
Description: This dyed bamboo placemat is richly colored and easy to clean.

Name: White Gold Place Setting
Description: Invokes the quiet beauty of an imperial garden at your dinner table.

Name: Bonsai Centerpiece
Description: How exquisite. You must take excellent care of this tiny tree. Now where are your tiny tools?

Name: Calligraphy Brush Set
Description: Practice your fanciest handwriting with this brush set. There is even a book with examples of all the letters in several styles.

Name: Letter-writing Set with Brush Drying Rack
Description: With this handy drip-dry brush rack, you'll always have a fresh brush ready to go.

Name: Brush Set with Parcels
Description: With this beautiful brush set with matching case, you, too, can succeed in the world of business.

Name: Tea Serving Set
Description: Serve up a moment of tranquility for yourself and your three closest friends.

Name: Tall Green Porcelain Vase
Description: This precious vase has changed hands many times over the centuries. Now, those hands are yours. Pay no attention to the rumors that it's cursed.

Name: Tall Red Porcelain Vase
Description: Created in China during the Jiajing period, vases like this one are wildly popular in royal courts around the world.

Name: Tall Black Porcelain Vase
Description: This rich black vase, decorated with gold leaf, is a relic of a bygone golden age of luxury.

Name: Tall Cream Porcelain Vase
Description: This vase glows with an understated brilliance, like a pearl.

Name: Tall White Porcelain Vase
Description: The delicate blue color of the flowers is made with cobalt ore, imported from a hot desert land.

Name: Red-lacquered Songbird Cage
Description: This beautiful birdcage is spotlessly clean and ready for a new tenant.

Name: Teak Painted Bamboo Blinds
Description: No view from any window could possibly be better than this.

Name: Ebony Painted Bamboo Blinds
Description: The best part of these blinds is that you can make the dragons disappear and reappear by tilting the slats.

Name: Rosewood Painted Bamboo Blinds
Description: Slatted blinds are a marvelous invention, allowing you to spy on your neighbors without them being able to see you in return.

Name: Jade Painted Bamboo Blinds
Description: Dragons are said to be able to create clouds with their breath. Drawing these blinds might increase the chance of rain.

Name: Goldenrod Brocade Drapes
Description: These silk drapes are a wonderful fusion of both Asian and European forms.

Name: Ruby Brocade Drapes
Description: The silver dragons embroidered into these drapes will protect your house from any strife that might try to enter through the window.

Name: Turquoise Brocade Drapes
Description: The same heavy elements used to create this turquoise dye, like lead and mercury, were also often brewed into popular 'health' elixirs.

Name: White Gold Brocade Drapes
Description: There are more than twenty Troy ounces of pure gold thread embroidered into each of these panels.

Name: Goldenrod Brocade Valance
Description: A golden swath of silk to hang in your window.

Name: Ruby Brocade Valance
Description: Aww, they're like tiny little drapes! That's adorable.

Name: Turquoise Brocade Valance
Description: Thanks to these short curtains, your house will stay nice and cool while the sun is high in the sky.

Name: White Gold Brocade Valance
Description: Placing jade near a window helps infuse incoming fresh air with its many virtues.

Name: Sentimental Silk Fans
Description: A famous dancer used this pair of fans in all her performances. When she retired, she passed them down to her granddaughter.

Name: Poignant Flower Hanging Basket
Description: In the language of flowers, this arrangement might symbolize hard-won, bittersweet wisdom.

Name: Decorative Root Ball
Description: This symbolic nest will encourage happiness to come roost in your home.

Name: Fragrant Incense Censer
Description: Incense has been burned in China since Neolithic times. Your house smells amazing now.

Name: "Pine Bonsai" Painting
Description: A black ink painting in a bamboo frame. The tight, precise brushstrokes that make up the pine needles have a courtly air.

Name: "Sunrise Over the Western Mountains" Painting
Description: A placid watercolor painting in a dark wood frame. The mountains wreathed in pre-dawn mists seem to promise the fresh start of a new day.

Name: "Improbable Pagoda" Painting
Description: A black ink painting in a bamboo frame. The four-floor pagoda depicted here is quite peculiar: nearly all pagodas have an uneven number of floors.

Name: "Clouds of Heaven" Painting
Description: A colorful blockprint in a dark wood frame. The skill of the printer is clearly displayed in the overlapping washes of color in the clouds.

Name: Huangjiu Amphora
Description: This sweet yellow wine is often referenced in classical Chinese literature. The highest quality huanjiu is aged in clay jars for up to twenty years.

Name: Teak Dresser
Description: Fashions change with the seasons, but a good teak dresser is timeless.

Name: Ebony Dresser
Description: Perhaps you could stage a fun diorama behind the center doors. No one else has to know.

Name: Rosewood Dresser
Description: The red color invites joy; the chrysanthemum drawer pulls denote longevity. With this dresser, you'll be happy forever.

Name: Jade Dresser
Description: The best jade is slightly translucent. Best put anything embarrassing at the bottom of the drawer.

Name: Teak Circular Curio Shelf
Description: A beautiful display for your smallest treasures, netsukes, tchotchkes, trinkets, gewgaws, knickknacks, bric-a-brac, or whatever is closest to your heart.

Name: Ebony Circular Curio Shelf
Description: Having this beautiful rosewood shelf on your wall is the perfect excuse to start some kind of whimsical collection.

Name: Rosewood Circular Curio Shelf
Description: This shelf might look dainty and delicate, but it can hold a great deal of heavy items and still remain on the wall.

Name: Jade Circular Curio Shelf
Description: This piece is more than a mere shelf. What you place on it is immaterial. In itself, it is a monument to the taste and authority of its owner.

Name: Teak Pedestal Shelf
Description: This handsome teak shelf is the perfect blend of form and function. Plus, it's naturally water-repellent.

Name: Ebony Pedestal Shelf
Description: The right-angled bracing below the shelf is not only pleasing to the eye, but also helps distribute the weight.

Name: Rosewood Pedestal Shelf
Description: The perfect place to display a priceless family heirloom, or perhaps an interesting rock you found on your morning walk.

Name: Jade Pedestal Shelf
Description: This exquisite shelf is only big enough to display one item. Choose carefully.

Name: Dynastic Stove
Description: There's no better place to prepare a heavenly feast.

Name: Four-tasseled Hanging Lantern
Description: The light from this lucky lantern is said to scare away hungry monsters that lurk in the darkness.

Name: Eight-tasseled Hanging Lantern
Description: This majestic eight-tasseled hanging lantern was once reserved for use only in the imperial palace.

Name: Temple Hanging Lantern
Description: The warm yellow glow of this iron lantern makes you feel safe, like someone is watching over you.

Name: Festival Hanging Lantern
Description: Every day is a party with this red paper lantern. There are no exceptions.

Name: Cutout Standing Lantern
Description: If you die out in the wilderness, this cheerful lantern will light a safe path for your soul to return.

Name: Round Standing Lantern
Description: Its unique round design allows it to shed its light equally in all directions.

Name: Temple Standing Lantern
Description: This brass lantern is a microcosm of a universe in harmony.

Name: Chrysanthemum Standing Lantern
Description: For some reason, the oil in this elaborate iron lantern seems to last twice as long as it should.

Name: Festival Wall-mounted Lantern
Description: This red triple lantern provides three times the protection against evil spirits.

Name: Iron-bound Wall-mounted Lantern
Description: With iron banding and a waterproof, fireproof coating, this lantern could withstand a hurricane.

Name: Simple Wall-mounted Lantern
Description: The simplicity of this paper lantern means that nothing will come between you and the light.

Name: Temple Wall-mounted Lantern
Description: There's no need to fear the dark, even if you're short on table space.

Name: Goldenrod Geometric Rug
Description: This silky-soft rug features a stylized keystone border. Its symmetrical perfection speaks to the mastery of the court artist who wove it.

Name: Ruby Geometric Rug
Description: The sharp contrast of the dark red and the bright silver calls to you in ways you never knew.

Name: Turquoise Geometric Rug
Description: Surround this jewel-toned silk rug with neutral colors to draw the viewer's eye.

Name: White Gold Geometric Rug
Description: The pure simplicity of the colors only highlights the pure mastery of the craftsmanship that is the majesty of this rug.

Name: Goldenrod Woven Floor Mat
Description: The bright orange of this woven mat always brings a smile to your face. You just can't help it. It's such a happy color.

Name: Ruby Woven Floor Mat
Description: The deepness of the red is so striking, no one will ever notice you swept all the dust under it.

Name: Turquoise Woven Floor Mat
Description: A traditional woven bamboo design, dyed a surprising blue-green. An easy-to-clean pop of color for your floor.

Name: White Gold Woven Floor Mat
Description: If you look carefully, you can see the delicate balance of gold and cream colors interwoven perfectly into what appears to be a solid color.

Name: Dynasty Storage Chest
Description:
A chest that grants access to your storage, and increases your storage by {[HouseItems.House_HousingItem_Storage_T3_Dynasty.StorageBonus / 10]} weight when placed in your home. 
Such fine craftsmanship, and a style rarely seen.

Name: Teak End Table
Description: This type of carved table is extremely popular among the merchant classes of Beijing.

Name: Ebony End Table
Description: This antique end table is in pristine condition. It would definitely spark a bidding war in the auction houses of Europe.

Name: Rosewood End Table
Description: Placing this end table next to your bed is sure to bring dreams of happiness.

Name: Jade End Table
Description: The latticework on this jade table is breathtaking. How did they carve that without cracking the stone?

Name: Teak Writing Desk
Description: It's easy to write poetry at this low desk. Being close to the earth provides inspiration.

Name: Ebony Writing Desk
Description: The elegant simplicity and graceful wear of this low writing desk whispers "old money".

Name: Rosewood Writing Desk
Description: If you want to do any writing at this desk, you will have to place a mat and sit on the floor. It's the proper method.

Name: Jade Writing Desk
Description: Any letters written at this commanding jade desk automatically become Proclamations.

Name: Teak Dining Table
Description: Teak trees don't grow on Aeternum, making this imported table especially prized.

Name: Ebony Dining Table
Description: This latticed table is an Aeternum original, created by a Chinese master craftsman. He wash up with the remains of his ship after a storm.

Name: Rosewood Dining Table
Description: The minimalist lines and understated aesthetic of this table places its origin squarely in the Ming Dynasty period.

Name: Jade Dining Table
Description: This solid jade table weighs over twelve hundred pounds. You should probably keep your cool, because this baby is unflippable.

Name: Graceful Teak Table
Description: The perfect place to put a pitcher of iced tea. The abalone top will help keep the ice from melting.

Name: Graceful Ebony Table
Description: This particular type of iridescent abalone used for this tabletop is unique to Aeternum.

Name: Graceful Rosewood Table
Description: Either they used a whole bunch of abalone to make the top for this table, or that was one really huge shellfish.

Name: Graceful Jade Table
Description: When the sunlight hits the abalone in exactly the right way, you can almost imagine a face just below the surface.

Name: Yellow Brass Lounge Bed
Description: Sleep a sleep as sweet as honey on this sun-kissed bed with blushing fabric. For even a warrior can have a soft side.

Name: Burnt Copper Lounge Bed
Description: This soothing blue bedding is optimal for lounging after a long day of smelting and blacksmithing.

Name: Deep Silver Lounge Bed
Description: A luxurious place to rest one's feet and escape the administrative toils of Aeternum.

Name: Light Pewter Lounge Bed
Description: Tired from a hard day of gathering? This will offer you the ultimate reprieve; almost like napping in a meadow.

Name: Centurion High Bed
Description: To show that even in sleep you rank the highest among all.

Name: Mediterranean High Bed
Description: Craftsmen are the backbone to society, and this bed keeps your backbone comfortable and aligned.

Name: Influential High Bed
Description: Purple is usually the color of nobility, and you will feel royal as can be cozied up on this bed.

Name: Verdant High Bed
Description: Bedding the colors of a bright summer day. Careful not to fall off the side!

Name: Cypress Wood Armchair
Description: Everyone should know their place, and you know yours is in a comfortable armchair. Take a seat. You deserve it.

Name: White Oak Wood Armchair
Description: Light wood and a yellow pillow to brighten any room. A welcome contrast to the workshops and crafting stalls.

Name: Walnut Wood Armchair
Description: An entirely new echelon of opulence awaits you on this armchair. Careful not to get too comfortable while doing paperwork.

Name: Olive Wood Armchair
Description: The earth tones of this armchair let the mind wander to matters of nature.

Name: Centurion Dining Chair
Description: Like territories fought and won, claim your rightful place at the head of the dining table.

Name: Mediterranean Dining Chair
Description: Pull this chair out from the table to present to a special guest.

Name: Influential Dining Chair
Description: First among equals? Maybe, but we all know who gets the best seat.

Name: Verdant Dining Chair
Description: Recline as you eat, for there is no greater joy than good rest and good food.

Name: Centurion Curule Seat
Description: Fight like a warrior, sit like a conqueror.

Name: Mediterranean Curule Seat
Description: Don't just put yourself on any old pedestal, put yourself on this one.

Name: Influential Curule Seat
Description: This gilded stool is stuffed with the feathers of a now-extinct goose. A seat of exquisite quality to match your intellect.

Name: Verdant Curule Seat
Description: Seat oneself with fellowship and break bread together.

Name: Cypress Wood Armoire
Description: For holding the fine linen that you use when hosting guests.

Name: White Oak Wood Armoire
Description: What could possibly be hidden within? Towels and clothes most likely.

Name: Walnut Wood Armoire
Description: Keep your secrets and your armoire locked up tight.

Name: Olive Wood Armoire
Description: If no one can see inside your armoire, no one can judge your fashion sense.

Name: Cypress Large Bookcase
Description: It could hold books well enough, but your spoils of war would look even better on these shelves.

Name: White Oak Large Bookcase
Description: Should you display your prized tools? Or your highest quality craftmanship? Decisions, decisions…

Name: Walnut Large Bookcase
Description: Someone as busy as you are needs to stay organized, and do it with style.

Name: Olive Large Bookcase
Description: Many a shelf to display whatever you please. Perhaps that rock collection you've been meaning to start.

Name: Cypress Small Bookcase
Description: Finally, somewhere to put your memoirs.

Name: White Oak Small Bookcase
Description: Shelves for you to store both Mediterranean recipe books and philosophy tomes.

Name: Walnut Small Bookcase
Description: A place for grimoires, books of shadows, and all manner of forbidden rites.

Name: Olive Small Bookcase
Description: Can contain books or adventuring tchotchkes, your preference.

Name: Cypress Family Shrine
Description: Eros: Love of Passion, for partners and marriage.

Name: White Oak Family Shrine
Description: Philia: Love of Friends, respecting equals and comrades.

Name: Walnut Family Shrine
Description: Agape: Love of Humankind, as perfect as a deity's love for humanity.

Name: Olive Family Shrine
Description: Storge: Love of Children, caring for the young and dependent.

Name: Cypress Chest of Drawers
Description: It is not polite to rifle through a stranger's drawers, but houses on Aeternum are open to all…

Name: White Oak Chest of Drawers
Description: Grandmothers are known to keep coin in these.

Name: Walnut Chest of Drawers
Description: What in Aeternum would be important enough to store here?

Name: Olive Chest of Drawers
Description: For the storage of underthings and love letters.

Name: Bronze Strobilus Charm
Description: Pine cones were considered fertility charms in ancient times. And a pine cone made of metal should be extra potent.

Name: Large Stone Brazier
Description: The coals glow lightly a top this well used brazier. It doesn't light up a room, but it will keep you warm.

Name: Hanging Barrel Cactus
Description: The best kind of cactus is one seen but not touched. And that is made all the easier when it is well out of reach.

Name: Hanging Opuntia Cactus
Description: An important part of the ecosystem, this type of cactus can provide food and shelter for many species of birds.

Name: Doric Style Display Column
Description: A stocky style of column from ancient Greece. Doric style Is usually rather plain, but not this one! This one is extra fancy with gold trimmings.

Name: Tuscan Style Display Column
Description: Many cultures of the Mediterranean loved the design of fluted columns, with each claiming to be the inventor of the style.

Name: Ionic Style Display Column
Description: An ancient Greek column styled with curling scroll-like patterns. Perfect for displaying things to do with literature or writing.

Name: Administrative Desk Scrolls
Description: There is a lot of paper work to do in an empire. Too much, in fact.

Name: Stone Display Platform
Description: A simple stone block with golden details. Can be used as a coffee table or display platform for your favorite decorations.

Name: Lattice Screen Divider
Description: It won't give you any privacy, but it will divide an area well enough.

Name: Potted Candelabra Cactus
Description: This species of cactus can grow to be huge. Taller than some houses! But this one is just a baby.

Name: Blooming Agave Plant
Description: It can take up to 40 years for an agave plant to bloom, and it only does it once, so you are luck to see this!

Name: Potted Mulberry Plant
Description: This bush would quickly grow into a tree if planted in the ground. But having portable fresh fruit is too convenient to pass up.

Name: Potted Opuntia Cactus
Description: This cactus can not only provide prickly protection for your home, but the broad flat pads can be harvested to make meals or medicine with.

Name: Potted Triangle Cactus
Description: Known for their three-pointed stalks, it's worth keeping around for the sweet fruit it can produce, even if you have to deal with the painful spines.

Name: Potted Saguaro Cactus
Description: A desert plant known to grow only in a small area of the Americas; it was shipped to Aeternum at the behest of an eccentric collector of exotic desert flora.

Name: Clean Serving Dishes
Description: Best not to let the dishes pile up, clean or otherwise.

Name: Meal Prep Dishes
Description: A lot of work goes into preparing a meal. So does a lot of dishes.

Name: Used Serving Dishes
Description: So many items tend to get used when making meals, and even more just to serve them.

Name: "Ceres - Goddess of Grain" Wall Fresco
Description: Adorn your home with the image of the goddess for good harvests. If it doesn't work, at least it is a nice decoration.

Name: "Mirroring Patterns" Wall Fresco
Description: Fresco styles is one of most difficult artistic skills to master. And only a true master could create such integrate mirroring patterns.

Name: "The Current of Time" Wall Fresco
Description: The eb and flow of time is depicted as repeating waves in this gold painted pattern. It is as if the eye of eternity is watching you.

Name: "The Duet" Wall Fresco
Description: A painting of a man and woman singing betwixt a floating lyre. Perhaps they are singing about the crazy magical instrument in front of them.

Name: Centurion Place Setting
Description: Any soldier worth their salt needs a place to eat their fill. An army marches on its stomach, after all.

Name: Mediterranean Place Setting
Description: The blues of the mat are so vibrant, you almost feel like you are eating your meal in the sky.

Name: Influential Place Setting
Description: This smart looking place setting is perfect for smart people. One cannot administrate on an empty stomach.

Name: Verdant Place Setting
Description: The vibrant green of the mat and scent of the wooden dishes stimulates your appetite.

Name: Ancient Pottery Wheel
Description: Why pay someone else for pottery, when you can make it yourself! The hardest part is starting. And finishing. And everything in-between.

Name: Carved Statue of Minerva
Description: A goddess to inspire you with handicrafts, the arts, and war. Embroidery and murder often overlap.

Name: Carved Statue of Caesar
Description: Which Caesar this statue depicts is unclear. There were so many.

Name: Carved Statue of Vesta
Description: The goddess of hearth and home, and one of several sisters of Jupiter. I wonder what book she has. Perhaps a cook book?

Name: Vase of Desert Senna Flowers
Description: Not only is this perennial flower an important food supply for desert dwelling insects, it looks gorgeous in this metal vase.

Name: Vase of Ocotillo Flowers
Description: These clustered red blooms look just like little torches. But please don't light these on fire. The plant would hate that.

Name: Carved Statue of Jupiter
Description: The main god of the roman pantheon. Son of Saturn, with several siblings, and lots and lots and lots of children. So many children.

Name: Legion Towel Rack
Description: Rome is famous for its baths, so of course you are going to need a towel.

Name: Centurion Valance
Description: A teal valance inspired by the type Centurions use in their war camp windows to look after their legion, but with style.

Name: Mediterranean Valance
Description: Gold valance whose silky threads herald from Lake Como. Only a little scratchy.

Name: Influential Valance
Description: Purple valance that helps you gain influence and wealth. Note: this statement has not been evaluated by the Aeternum Decor Council.

Name: Verdant Valance
Description: A green valence that won't protect your home from sand or sun, but it looks nice.

Name: Centurion Tapestry
Description: A red tapestry that's a replica of one that was won from a Centurion in a battle. One wonders why they had a tapestry on the battleground.

Name: Mediterranean Tapestry
Description: A blue tapestry of lineage, inspiring respect from all who see it.

Name: Influential Tapestry
Description: A purple tapestry of royal descent that has been missing from the palaces of the Old World for some time now.

Name: Verdant Tapestry
Description: A yellow tapestry that won't show all the sand that's likely to collect on it.

Name: Centurion Curtains
Description: Red curtains that represent the blood spilled in battles with the Corrupted Legion. You can't even see the blood stains!

Name: Mediterranean Curtains
Description: Covering your windows with these keeps the house nice and cool.

Name: Influential Curtains
Description: Only peasants have bare walls. Your walls will have these extremely lovely purple curtains, so everyone can tell you have money to spare.

Name: Verdant Curtains
Description: Proud, vibrate curtains of a stunning yellow color. They both keep out the sand and have a SPF rating of 80.

Name: "Glory to Sol" Inset Emblem
Description: With the glory of the sun god adorning your walls, who knows what you can accomplish!

Name: West Flowing Solis Currents
Description: A gold metal decoration depicting waves in sunlight. When you have these up, you can just go with the flow.

Name: East Flowing Solis Currents
Description: These golden waves flow so elegantly. You can almost imagine the rolling sea on a bright sunny day when gazing at them.

Name: West Flowing Selene Currents
Description: A silver metal decoration depicting waves in moonlight. These would be good to depict ocean waves in a play.

Name: East Flowing Selene Currents
Description: One is reminded of the cool sea ablaze with the light of the moon. And all without the wet and water.

Name: Rojo-Levantina Marble Top Dresser
Description: Perfect for the serving of after-battle drinks.

Name: Lazulite Marble Top Dresser
Description: Marked with the seal of a famous general, though no one can remember his name.

Name: Amethyst Marble Top Dresser
Description: Deep within the back of the drawers is a secret compartment. What will you use yours for?

Name: Serpentine Marble Top Dresser
Description: As green as any plant you may wish to place atop it.

Name: Cypress Wooden Wall Shelf
Description: For proudly displaying trophies of war.

Name: White Oak Wooden Wall Shelf
Description: Can be placed high or low on the walls of your home for showing off items.

Name: Walnut Wooden Wall Shelf
Description: Show the world that you have taste and that you know how to flaunt it.

Name: Olive Wooden Wall Shelf
Description: The perfect place for all those important letters from the Magistrate you're not responding to.

Name: Centurion Concrete Stove
Description: Be sure to oil your pans before use unless you want the food sticking to the bottom and burning.

Name: Mediterranean Concrete Stove
Description: These clay pots were made by the finest of artisans, and do well for preparing a fine meal after a hard day's work.

Name: Influential Concrete Stove
Description: A stove capable of cooking for a whole household of guests at your weekly company meetings.

Name: Verdant Concrete Stove
Description: Happiness is the smell of fresh rations after a long day of adventuring.

Name: Yellow Brass Hanging Oil Lamp
Description: See the whites of your enemy's eyes by illuminating your rooms with this bright fixture.

Name: Burnt Copper Hanging Oil Lamp
Description: Don't forget to fill up the oil every so often if you want these at their brightest.

Name: Deep Silver Hanging Oil Lamp
Description: Show off the latest in lighting technology and everyone will know what a futurist you are.

Name: Light Pewter Hanging Oil Lamp
Description: Never trip over your furniture in the dark again! (Unless you forget to replace the wicks.)

Name: Yellow Brass Tall Oil Lamp
Description: Is this the one you're supposed to rub three times? How shiny does it need to get before you get some wishes?

Name: Burnt Copper Tall Oil Lamp
Description: Comes with a handy pull-chain to quickly extinguish or ignite the oil.

Name: Deep Silver Tall Oil Lamp
Description: Bring the blue flames of the Ancient Guardians to the comfort of your home. After all, someone of your stature deserves it.

Name: Light Pewter Tall Oil Lamp
Description: A special copper powder mixed in the oil burns green, and makes for an amusing conversation starter with this lamp.

Name: Yellow Brass Short Oil Lamp
Description: Fits perfectly on a bedside table and quick to light when it is your shift for the night watch.

Name: Burnt Copper Short Oil Lamp
Description: The dark copper is striking. Be careful and try not to burn your fingers when lighting this lamp.

Name: Deep Silver Short Oil Lamp
Description: Holds a special oil that burns a bright blue flame. Perfect to set the mood for administrative work.

Name: Light Pewter Short Oil Lamp
Description: Flickers of bright green flame is reminiscent of fields of green grass blowing in the wind.

Name: Yellow Brass Wall Brazier
Description: Maker not responsible for ceiling burns if you place it too high on the wall.

Name: Burnt Copper Wall Brazier
Description: Red is the color of passion, and this flame is as wild and free as your most passionate dreams.

Name: Deep Silver Wall Brazier
Description: They mix azoth with the coals so the blue flames really strands out. It shows you have money to burn. Literally.

Name: Light Pewter Wall Brazier
Description: The light shifts from yellow to green, but lights up your room all the same.

Name: Centurion Woven Rug
Description: The geometric shapes on this rug contrast with the sheathes of wheat, symbolizing that armies need both food and weapons to be affective.

Name: Mediterranean Woven Rug
Description: This blue is even bluer than Azoth and the yellow the color of fields of grain.

Name: Influential Woven Rug
Description: There is no better way to pronounce your wealth than a rug of purple.

Name: Verdant Woven Rug
Description: Animals love to lay on this as it reminds them of grass.

Name: Legion Storage Chest
Description:
A chest that grants access to your storage, and increases your storage by {[HouseItems.house_housingitem_storage_t3_legion.StorageBonus / 10]} weight when placed in your home. 
This is the most solid and sturdy chest you have ever seen.

Name: Rojo-Levantina Marble Bedside Table
Description: The depiction on the bedside table is a mystery to you. Who could these figures be?

Name: Lazulite Marble Bedside Table
Description: Placed at the side of the bed, this table shows two people amidst conversation.

Name: Amethyst Marble Bedside Table
Description: In a luxurious purple a man and woman surround an instrument of power.

Name: Serpentine Marble Bedside Table
Description: The shadows of two humans are cast upon this bedside table, leaving you with more questions than answers.

Name: Cypress Wooden Desk
Description: Here you may sit and write to your company colleagues about the next war or invasion.

Name: White Oak Wooden Desk
Description: This wooden desk is firm enough to take the furious scratchings of your pen to parchment as you write jeers about the other factions.

Name: Walnut Wooden Desk
Description: For the writing of love letters, music, and poetry betwixt writing laws and declarations.

Name: Olive Wooden Desk
Description: The drawers contain everything you need to draft up that next composition or maps.

Name: Mosaiced Cypress Wooden Stand
Description: The tiles on this mosaic were smoothed down by a skilled craftsperson.

Name: Mosaiced White Oak Wooden Stand
Description: This wooden stand can hold any memento of import, or not-so-import.

Name: Mosaiced Walnut Wooden Stand
Description: The dark tiles entrance the viewer. How did they get it so perfectly circular?

Name: Mosaiced Olive Wooden Stand
Description: For the playing of games with friends, be it Ludus Latrunculi, Knucklebones, or even Tic-Tac-Toe.

Name: Rojo-Levantina Marble Dining Table
Description: Make yourself the host with the most when you serve upon this marble tabletop.

Name: Lazulite Marble Dining Table
Description: The blue marble is as deep and enchanting as the rough seas around Aeternum.

Name: Amethyst Marble Dining Table
Description: Dinner party dishes have never looked so good as they look atop this table.

Name: Serpentine Marble Dining Table
Description: Not even the fields of Windsward are this green!

Name: Cypress Wood Small Table
Description: A small table versatile enough to be placed in any kind of room. Now what to place upon it?

Name: White Oak Wood Small Table
Description: The white oak of this table is so smooth you can run your hand over the top without getting a splinter.

Name: Walnut Wood Small Table
Description: This small table holds a great deal of power in its presence, and can hold aloft even the heaviest of lamps.

Name: Olive Wood Small Table
Description: The sight of this olive wood table fills you with a nostalgia for home you will never be able to quench.

Name: Springtide Banner
Description: No matter the seasons, this flower will be there for you.

Name: Barrel of Flowers
Description: Good thing nothing on Aeternum ever truly dies or these flowers may not have survived this long.

Name: Crate of Flowers
Description: Unlike those terrible wasps, the bee's these flowers attract are rather pleasant.

Name: Pot of Wispy Blooms
Description: Watch out for the Wispy Wasps!

Name: Springtide Ceiling Light
Description: The layered design of this lantern casts rings of light below that twirl in a breeze.

Name: Springtide Wall Light
Description: This glowing lantern is fortunately not a real jellyfish and can sting no one. Although it could still drop on you.

Name: Sacks of Pigment
Description: These festive colors are sure to get everywhere, and remind you of spring months from now when you least expect it.

Name: Pinwheel
Description: Rachel thinks this is just the best.

Name: Memento Amissum
Description: Erstwhile a sweet memento of one's life, now a sour reminder of those lost.

Name: Trophy of Blood of the Sands
Description:
A trophy that inspires you a little bit when completing Seasonal content, awarded for completing Chapter 4 of the Season 2 Season Journey.


Only works when placed in your home, and does not count against your trophy limit.

Grants a 5% bonus to all Season XP gained during Season 2.

At the end of Season 2, this trophy will lose its power but remain in your possession.

Name: Sandwurm Egg of the Long Journey
Description: A Sandwurm Egg with an extra tough exterior. Received from the Season 2 Season Journey.

Name: Sandwurm Egg of the Oasis
Description: An Sandwurm Egg encased in an ornate shell. Received from the Season 2 Season Pass.

Name: Sandwurm Egg of Blood and Sand
Description: A grisly and bloodied Sandwurm Egg. Received from completion of the Blood of the Sands Season Narrative.

Name: Sandwurm Egg of the Protector
Description: A distinctly earthy and lush Sandwurm Egg. Received from the Siege of Sulfur World Event.

Name: Sandwurm Egg of the Hatchery
Description: A beautifully decorated Sandwurm Egg. Received from The Hatchery Trial.

Name: Memory of the Fallen
Description: It’s not much but it’s all that’s left. May it serve in their memory.

Name: Throne of the Minotaur
Description: Though you may not be as large, you are certainly just as mighty.

Name: Pile of Bananas
Description: This amount of bananas is just... ridiculous.

Name: Beast's Nest
Description: The prefered resting place of ground dwelling birds and marooned sailors.

Name: Hanging Jungle Vines
Description: Not strong enough to swing on but that doesn't mean you can't try.

Name: Tattered Banner
Description: Though weathered and worn, at least it hangs with some of its original pride intact.

Name: Statue of an Anubian Brute
Description: You can almost feel the shuddering step of this towering figure.

Name: Statue of a Lost Archer
Description: Even though it can't possibly move, it's best to avoid standing in front of it just in case.

Name: Statue of a Lost Axeman
Description: Even though it can't possibly move, it's best to avoid standing in front of it just in case.

Name: Statue of an Alpha Wolf
Description: Though only stone, this beast appears as if it'll pounce at any moment.

Name: Statue of a Rousing Swordsman
Description: The empassioned shout of this forgotten warrior silently echoes through the annals of time.

Name: Monstera Foliage
Description: Despite the name, it's not actually monsterous. Probably.

Name: Bulbous Chameleon Cordata
Description: This standing cordata is covered in bioluminecent fungi.

Name: Giant Corpus Lily
Description: These massive lilies are not only beautiful but soothing. Its pollen is a strong relaxant that causes small animals and other prey to fall into its narrow acid wells.

Name: Dragontail Thuja
Description: Legends say young dragons are very shy and bury themselves into the earth to where only their tails remain visable.

Name: Tufted-Tail Bush
Description: The plush down of this plant has gained popular usage as an alternative to furs and feathers. It's also said to bring good luck.

Name: Throne of the Hollow
Description: Has great back support.

Name: Baalphazu's Offering
Description: One should not always follow the light.

Name: Summoning Circle
Description: Four out of five family members agree the guests summoned from this are better guests than your inlaws.

Name: Basket of Treats
Description: It's got all kinds of candy in here… even the bad ones.

Name: Trophy of the Elysian Wilds
Description:
A trophy that inspires you a little bit when completing Seasonal content, awarded for completing Chapter 4 of the Season 3 Season Journey.


        Only works when placed in your home, and does not count against your trophy limit.

        Grants a 5% bonus to all Season XP gained during Season 3.

        At the end of Season 3, this trophy will lose its power but remain in your possession.
